paragraph_descriptions: Do you feel stuck? Do you need a sanctuary where you can gain perspective?  I offer adults a safe place in which to experience relief and the space to gain confidence, calm, and clarity. If you've been dealing with issues such as anxiety, low self-esteem, grief, loss, creative blocks, family issues, and trauma, please know that you can feel freer, happier, and more secure. I use a variety of techniques including EMDR to explore connections between present struggles and past experiences, to increase body awareness, and to help clients gain a more powerful sense of themselves, allowing them to create healthier patterns in their lives.I offer therapy online and in-person in Davis, CA. In addition to weekly, ongoing sessions, I also provide Adjunct EMDR for clients who already have a therapist but want to focus on resolving a particular issue or incident. And for people who prefer a concentrated therapy experience, I offer a package of three 90-Minute EMDR sessions (when appropriate).If you're motivated to feel better now, please contact me for a free 15-minute phone consultation.  I see clients from all over California online and locally in my Davis, California office.  Please feel free to reach out with any questions. You can feel better.

These are unprecedented times and we are facing the aftermath of a global trauma. You may be feeling grief, loss, burnout, depression, anxiety, or you may have no clue what it is you're feeling. I am here to hold space for you as we make our way through this existential crisis.Effective therapy must involve both mind and body. When we pay attention to our bodies we can begin to untangle places where we are emotionally or cognitively stuck. Working somatically will create space for profound growth that is often untapped using only traditional therapy modalities.In addition to traditional talk therapy, I utilize Somatic Experiencing, meditation, relaxation, movement, and mindfulness techniques in my practice. I have additional training in helping clients integrate non-ordinary states of consciousness.

Hello, I am Judy Moore. I bring an exciting range of life experience and professional training to the therapy setting. I honor the stories and narrations you share with me in therapy and believe that the slow formation of trust between us creates a sacred ground for healing. Through this relationship built on trust and respect, you can find a way to more confidently navigate your life in a calmer way. I enjoy working with mood disturbance, anxiety, relationship issues and existential life situations. I am particularly fascinated by cultural diversity and am committed to helping you grow in a supportive and encouraging environment.I specialize in exploring core issues that have a profound influence on the way you think, feel and behave in your life and in relationships. With a loving heart and gentle prompting, my goal is to help guide you to a life of greater ease and comfort that feels better.Having been raised in a bicultural, European household, I treasure diversity and have respect for each person's uniqueness. I am aware that I learned my greatest lessons from people most different from me and I try to create a safe environment in which you can explore your individuality.

I work with adolescents and young adults.  I specialize in working with adolescents and young adults who are having a particularly difficult time with major life transitions. I also work with clients struggling with depression, anxiety, difficulties with relationships and individuals who are struggling with a particularly difficult period or event in their lives.  Regardless of what I am helping with, my treatment begins and ends with the therapeutic relationship.  My first priority in treatment is creating a safe, warm and caring environment for my client from which all other work is built on.My work is influenced by current neurobiological research and research regarding our early attachments to our caregivers.  My work concentrates on understanding, strengthening and often repairing the connection between our mind and our body.My practice is fluid and will often include more active therapeutic methods for those children and adolescents who are hard to reach and connect with verbally.

I believe that you have the wisdom and capability to live the life you desire and deserve.  I can help you tap into your individual strengths to overcome challenges and create a more meaningful, connected, authentic and fulfilling life.  My approach to therapy is client-focused, open and compassionate.I work with children, adolescents, adults and couples in addressing anxiety, relationship challenges, life transitions, communication issues, depression, stress management and other concerns.Thank you for taking the time to learn about my practice.  I look forward to an opportunity to work with you.

𝗔𝗧𝗧𝗘𝗡𝗧𝗜𝗢𝗡 𝗔𝗗𝗨𝗟𝗧𝗦 & 𝗖𝗢𝗨𝗣𝗟𝗘𝗦: Does it feel like painful experiences of the past are still impacting you?  Is it hard to connect with others, communicate effectively, and feel safe in relationships and in the world?  No matter how hard you try, are you stuck in the same pattern?  Does all of this confusion and hurt leave you with feelings of shame, depression, anxiety, and fear?  Are these feelings starting to impact your sense of self or your views on relationships?  When we experience trauma or life challenges, it can feel like we’re in a cycle of suffering.  It doesn't have to be this way. 𝗜 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗵𝗲𝗹𝗽.In my work, I help adults, teens and couples create the safety, joy and calm that feels outside of their grasp. To help you on your healing path, we'll work together using a compassionate and honest approach. With your knowledge of yourself and my clinical insight, training and experience, the wounds of the past can heal in the present. Change is possible.The journey you're taking now, I've had to walk as well.  I'm not going to ask you to do something that I have not done.  The skills you will learn, I use daily.  Trauma and relational wounds can heal.  They don't need to be a life sentence.  Thank you for your courage in reaching out.  Let's use this bravery to uncover your fullest potential.

As a licensed Marriage Family Therapist with over 25 years experience in the mental health field, my goal is to help individuals, couples and families to sort through difficult personal or work related  issues. If you feel stuck and are dealing with relationship issues, anxiety, depression, grief, illness, work and life transitions, having someone to help you address problems when you need it most can enhance self awareness and bring clarity to your life. Please acknowledge yourself for having the courage to seek help now.I work with you in a caring way to enhance your insight and discover effective, healthy coping methods for change. I look forward to assisting you to explore options, enhance your self awareness, and feel better.  Please call, email your questions, or request a free 20 minute phone consultation.Individuals and couples sometimes notice their personal problems affecting their work or vice versa. I have experience to help you sort through these issues. As Robert Frost said, "The best way out is through." My goal is to help you feel empowered and communicate what it is you truly want.

As our changing world becomes more complex, it's important to take stock of what matters in life.  When emotional struggles result in destructive behaviors, anxiety, and depression, we loose sight of our best selves. Meanwhile, seeking out help for these issues can be awkward! Your comfort in this process is my priority.  Our time together will be based on your goals, your concerns, and your unique personality.  I work with a wide range of clients including those of all types of cognitive or physical abilities, cultural backgrounds, religious / non-religious beliefs, gender identities, and sexual orientations.

What goes on in your mind, plays out in your body, and becomes your reality in your world. Whether you are entering therapy for the first time or you are looking to refine changes in your life, you are starting on a journey of self discovery which is deeply personal and courageous.  Each person arrives with their own unique life story, strengths, barriers and goals.  Therapy is a collaborative process.  I believe my role is to create a non-judgmental, warm, respectful, and safe environment.Building a strong therapeutic relationship is an important foundation in which you will learn to become more flexible in your problem-solving approaches.  Engaging in a curious manner to understand old patterns, behaviors and thoughts, you will learn practical skills in managing symptoms of depression, anxiety, and other life stressors.It truly is my privilege and honor to hear your story and assist you in your journey.  I invite you to contact me directly for specific information regarding my practice and experience.  Working together, I know we can find better approaches to coping with life stressors and increasing your fulfillment of your life goals.

I believe that people experience healing in and through relationships. Brené Brown defines connection as “the energy that exists between people when they feel seen, heard, and valued; when they derive sustenance and strength from the relationship”. Therapy can be a powerful, safe space to experience that connection both as individuals and partnerships.As both a couples and individual therapist I practice emotion-focused therapy (EFT) with influences from both attachment and family system theories.  Additionally, I am a certified Integrated Intimacy Professional; I specialize in bringing a holistic focus to helping couples work through sex and intimacy issues.I offer a free 20 minute phone consultation for prospective clients to see if therapy with me feels like a good fit. I am currently only accepting new clients via Teletherapy due to COVID-19. I am a licensed MFT in Washington state and a licensed MFT associate in California and happily work with clients from both areas.

Love Bigger. Really! Enrich your relationships. Reclaim your vitality. Open your heart to the world (again). Counseling is my calling. I offer over a decade of counseling and intuitive coaching expertise to guide your way. Let’s shift your pain into wisdom, temper your negative thoughts, celebrate your emotions, and honor your healing as a rite of passage. There's lots of room here to bring your whole self: your political beliefs, gender identity, relationship configuration, spiritual beliefs, all of you is welcome here.Transformation is possible. It requires you to risk opening up to joy. So... how do you want to grow? You don’t have to figure it out alone. Book a free session and get some joyful, skillful support, wherever you are on your journey. No sales pitch. No hype. Just a great chance to see if we connect and if this approach is right for you.CLIENT TESTIMONIALS: “leaf helped me plant flowers in some of the darkest places of my past.” -ML __“leaf is sensitive to each client’s cultural contexts… he helped me appreciate myself and my relationship with the world more than I thought possible.”-RR

I believe that you are intrinsically worthy of love and belonging but I know that often we are made to believe that being ourselves is not good enough. Self-love and acceptance can begin within this space; a place where all feel welcomed and relaxed, free from cultural and societal expectations.  I'm glad you're here.Hello and welcome to my practice! My name is Ema Miille and I am an Associate Clinical Social Worker, supervised by Loriene Honda, Ph.D., Ed.M., located in Davis, California. I work with children, adolescents, and adults with a variety of concerns including anxiety, depression, eating disorders and trauma. Beginning therapy can be hard, but you've got this!

My ideal client is any person(s) desiring to be a better person today than yesterday. I have extensive background working with men, women, teenagers, families, college-based students, athletes (collegiate and professional) seeking psycho-therapeutic intervention in areas, but not limited to anxiety, grief and loss processing, marriage counseling, chemical dependency, athletic consulting, performance-based psychology, depression, career counseling, anger management, and group counseling. A wide range of therapeutic modalities are practiced.My specialty is providing a empathetic therapeutic alliance with my clientele. My clients are their greatest experts, whereby allowing me to journey with them personally as support. Client feedback reveals a very calm and attuning demeanor in support of expressed needs and life challenges. A broad experience base, includes counseling, law enforcement/ legal expertise; licensed ministry experience; collegiate and professional experience. Anticipate PhD completion in performance-based psychology by 2020. A divorcee and a father of two boys (youngest deceased at age 23, in 2013).

I offer a warm, compassionate, down-to-earth, non-judgmental style that lends itself to creating a safe and trusting therapeutic environment for healing, growth and change. I work actively and collaboratively with you to develop an integrated approach to treatment that is tailored to suit your unique concerns and goals. We may explore historical and current emotions, thoughts and behavior patterns that are keeping you from more meaningful relationships, esteem and the quality of life you want. I encourage your feedback and am flexible to work with your changing needs.I have over 25 years of experience providing individual therapy for adults of all ages. Prior to private practice, I worked at the UC Davis Counseling Center and have extensive experience with college students, staff and faculty. I utilize a variety of current research-based theoretical perspectives, including attachment, relational, interpersonal and psychodynamic models.I have particular interests in the areas of integration, trauma, relationships, life transitions, and identity. I have specialized training and experience helping LGBTQ+ folks. I value and enjoy my therapeutic connection with clients and consider it an honor to support and assist people on their path toward greater life fulfillment.
issues: Queer, Non-binary, Pansexual, Asexual and Hetero

paragraph_descriptions: Sometimes it feels like your love of food and your hate for parts of your body are locked in constant battle. You got drafted into a war you didn't ask for. All you want is peace, or at least diplomacy. Somewhere along the way your stress focused in on eating, and now you feel stuck. Anxiety and depression have taken over; the enemy is winning. I've been there, and I'm here to help you negotiate the end of that war going on inside. Lets get to work on your relationship with yourself. After all, you are one of the most important people in your life!As we do that work together, you'll find your relationship with your body and your eating will come into alignment. You'll be able to enjoy food you love, find physical movement that brings you happiness, and find peace from that constant inner turmoil. Your anxiety will diminish, your mood will lift, and engaging in your life will feel more exciting.At Embodied Wisdom Counseling our services are done via telehealth, which gives you easier access with no drive time. We are fully licensed to practice therapy in California, Texas, and Ohio. We also work through referral with some wonderful registered dietitians and psychiatrists if/when needed. Please check us out at EmbodiedWisdomCounseling.com.

I will help you create a calm and safe space so you explore your relationships with yourself and others.  This safety will help you open up more vulnerable experiences which I can help you process and have a greater insight and relief from your emotional pain.  Emotionally focused therapy (EFT) and EMDR and EMDR M (Modified, Laurel Parnell’s training) attachment trauma therapy help you process stuck patterns either from trauma or "negative cycles" with loved ones or with your inner self.  These cycles repeat endlessly and can be very distressing.  I work extensively with shame and the inner critic to help you settle and open up moreI am an advance student in my spiritual practice of inquiry and mindfulness in the Ridhwan school in Berkeley for 18 years now.  I have advanced training in Emotionally Focused Therapy (EFT) for couples.  I also have advanced trauma training in EMDR (M) to help process and integrate past traumas with emphasis on attachment taught by Laurel Parnell.I have a strong love or art in the form or poetry and creative writing.  I also paint and draw in acrylic and pencil with ink.  This love of the arts helps me open to the nonverbal and creative acts we all engage which help us communicate the parts or us that often do not have a voice.

A favorite quote of mine is, "The truth always happens." Too often, our present truth is filled with suffering and anxiety. But we can shape our truth, to better cope with disorder or overcome pain and trauma. The therapeutic process provides insight into behaviors and actions that allows for growth in self and relationships.  I specialize in working with children, adolescents and adults of all backgrounds, helping clients and families to understand a range of behaviors and disorders. Working together, clients learn to recognize feelings, relate them to behaviors, and develop tools to recreate their own truth.I have a youthful spirit and am open and honest with my clients, always working to provide an environment conducive for growth. I offer a sliding payment scale, so that clients can afford the help they deserve.

Hi, and welcome. If you are reading this you are in preparation to take a big step to create important change in your life. I commend you. 

I specialize in treating chronic and acute PTSD resulting from both single and childhood trauma events; anxiety disorders, loss/bereavement and pain management. I am also a skilled couple therapist.  
As a seasoned professional with ample life experience. I hold a doctoral degree from Fielding Graduate University and am dual-licensed as a Clinical Psychologist and as a Marriage and Family Therapist. I am here to help you become your personal best with research driven treatments.My chosen therapeutic modalities include Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing (EMDR), and Emotion-Focused Couple Therapy (EFT). These models are research driven interventions.My clinical background is fortified by over twenty-five years experience in a variety of health settings. I am a EMDR Certified therapist and Consultant to other professionals. As a Certified Emotional Focused Couple Therapist, I have ample experience to help you create safety and connection in your relationships..

I welcome the opportunity to work with young adults to older adults to help to develop a preferred self.  I know that developing an identity as a young adult can be challenging. Professionals may find it exhausting to have a work-life balance, or may be seeking meaning in their lives. I appreciate and value the intersections of our identities and how we navigate our lives. I work in a relational way holding clients in positive regard, attuning to you, and helping to identify internal and external resources to apply.I can empathize with the challenges of seeking a meaningful life and how it can be a process. I  see myself as non judgmental when in relationship with diverse individuals. I am certified in Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing (EMDR) often used to address trauma.

Are stressors, challenges, or unresolved issues from your past holding you back and causing strain in your relationships? Are you seeking compassionate, client-focused therapy in an atmosphere of unconditional acceptance? I understand that each individual's story is unique, and so are their responses to life's challenges. I specialize in working with individuals (adult and teen) and couples regardless of background, who are navigating the complexities of depression, anxiety, trauma and PTSD, strained relationships, intimacy difficulties, and infidelity.Grounded in trauma-informed therapy techniques that incorporate somatic and mindfulness practices, my goal is to help you tackle underlying causes of your struggles and integrate strategies to maintain your emotional and psychological well-being. I primarily use attachment theory combined with evidence-based approaches such as IFS, EFT and Narrative Therapy.I understand that your journey is unique, and I am committed to walking alongside you every step of the way. If you're prepared and motivated to embark on a transformative quest toward healing, self-discovery, and stronger relationships, let's work together.    Are you ready? You don’t have to navigate this journey alone.

As your therapist my goal is to create a safe and comfortable environment where individuals ranging from adolescents to young adults (ages 14 to 24) can feel heard. Whether you are struggling with maneuvering through obstacles, going through major life transitions or are trying to learn how to handle anxious and depressive symptoms all are welcome here. If you are motivated, self aware, cognizant of your feelings, open minded, hesitant, scared, uncertain, confused and overwhelmed then therapy is the place for you. I offer both in person and Telehealth sessions and have a range of availability!If you are a student then the cost per session is $30.Helping people with their mental health and breaking both the societal and cultural stigma surrounding it has always been something I was passionate about. Therapy is a place where you are at your most vulnerable and I’d be honored to be allowed into that space of vulnerability alongside you so that I can assist you in accomplishing your goals.

Entering therapy can be a frightening and vulnerable experience. Please honor your effort in taking a step forward. I provide a warm and accepting environment to allow for honest and open exploration of your concerns and experiences. If you are struggling with personal or relationship issues, anxiety, depression, or grief, I can assist you in sorting through the  complexities and in reaching clear goals and attainable solutions to help you feel better, enjoy more satisfying relationships,  and live a more fulfilling life.I specialize in Emotionally Focused Therapy for couples (EFT). I have been certified for several years based on successful completion of extensive training and experience assisting at Externships and Core Skills workshops aimed at teaching therapists the EFT model. I am available at a variety of times throughout the week and warmly welcome your call.

I provide psychotherapeutic services for children, teens and adults in Davis, CA.   Prior to private practice I worked in community mental health and residential treatment.     I use a person-centered approach, tailoring therapy to each individual’s needs and strengths.  I have particular interest in working with young people and their parents through the ups and downs, developmental challenges, and stresses of growing up.  Clients have shared that I have an easy, down to earth, warm and relational approach.  I have received training in a variety of Play Therapy modalities, Trauma Focused Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (TF-CBT), Early Childhood/Family Mental Health, The Incredible Years (parenting program), and Attachment-Focused EMDR.    Thank you for taking the time to learn more about my practice, please contact me if you would like to discuss working together.

I enjoy working with clients who are experiencing roadblocks on their path to a more fulfilled life. Barriers to wellness are not limited to the mental realm and may include physical issues, sexual issues, relationship issues and spiritual issues. These issues interrelate and thus must all be addressed holistically. The symptom is not the cause and is often key in figuring out where the problem resides. I believe in the power of the human beings to heal themselves. I see my role as helping identify solutions and offering tools for personal growth and healing. I seek to empower my clients as they heal, grow and develop resilience.My main approaches are Reality Therapy and Naturopathic Psychotherapy, a holistic form of psychotherapy evaluating the interrelatedness of the mental, physical and spiritual realms. In addition to being a licensed Marriage and Family Therapist, I have a master's degree in Psychology and a doctorate in Naturopathy for Health Care Professionals.For over 20 years, I've been providing a wide range of psychotherapy services to adults, teens and couples in a safe, warm and confidential environment. My practice is designed to support you on your journey of healing and growth. Additionally, I specialize in working with alternative lifestyle communities, including the polyamorous and BDSM communities.

I view each person as an expert of their own experience, with therapy as a collaborative process focusing on an enduring connectedness with others and the world. I use an empathic, compassionate, and direct approach, which may allow for safety and trust to develop. Supported by my undergraduate training at San Francisco State University, and graduate training at the California Institute of Integral Studies, I believe in the importance of socio-cultural, environmental experiences as they contribute to the innate resilience and compassion within each person.I have over 10 years of clinical experience providing mental health services in both urban and rural communities. My treatment approach is eclectic, and while attending to the unique clinical needs of each individual, the treatment focus that may integrate solution-focused, motivational interviewing, cognitive-behavioral, mindfulness, and/or interpersonal, relational, psychodynamic approaches.Nature has been shown to support an individual's sense of well-being in the world. Connecting with elements of nature may also provide a sense of connectedness, safety and protection. If you are interested, we may incorporate your unique connection with Nature as part of the therapy process.

I create a healing space for those who are struggling with anxiety, depression and managing their emotions.  These issues can cause stress in your daily life and in relationship with others. I do believe that there is a way to honor our lived experiences while learning new skills to help manage your emotional life. As a therapist I combine an eclectic approach from many different modalities with training and experience in DBT, CBT and trauma informed therapy. My goal is to partner with you, building a strong therapeutic relationship through being empathetic, honest and having a good sense of humor. I know how challenging it can be to find the right therapist.  Please send me a message and we can speak more in depth about what you are looking for in your journey.          P.S. (It is easier for me to reply to emails than voicemails.)

As you start on the path to motherhood are you feeling anxious, sad, perhaps ashamed or just not yourself?  It can be frustrating, draining, overwhelming, and at times heartbreaking.  This is likely not how you thought it would be.  It feels like it should be a natural, seamless process filled with joyous moments. Unfortunately, it's often not the reality and I am here to support you regardless of where you are in this journey.  Imagine how it would feel to be the best version of yourself.  To enter motherhood confident, happy, and calm. Together we can get you feeling that way.My focus is on women experiencing infertility, perinatal loss and postpartum depression and I am certified in perinatal mental health. In our sessions, you will feel listened to and supported while we work together to help you navigate this time in your life and get ready to meet the challenges associated with becoming a mother.This is an area that has always been of profound interest to me.  It can be a particularly vulnerable time in a woman's life, and it's my honor to support you through this process.  Let's have you start feeling better today.  Click on my website for more information or call me to set up a free phone consultation.  I look forward to working with you.
issues: Grief Support following pregnancy or infant loss

paragraph_descriptions: Do you sometimes feel alone in your pain, or worry that no one really understands you?  It's not easy navigating the demands of life including family, relationships and work. Expressing yourself is difficult when you can't find the right words to say. Having to feel like you have to be the strong one every moment of the day is exhausting, or the one that holds it together for everybody. It can take a toll on your mind and body. You can be your own worst critic although you try your best to do everything right.You're needing support with the self critic, the negative thoughts, and comparing yourself to others. Imagine being able to calm those anxious thoughts and be in the present moment as well as connect with your body. You have the ability to take control and learn how to offer yourself tools that will help you connect to your authentic self.It is important to make sure that you feel comfortable and safe in therapy. And once you feel these things, you can open up, without feeling judged or criticized. This allows you the ability to change, grow and heal by being heard and seen unconditionally and authentically. I welcome you to reach out if you feel that we may be a good fit.

You are looking for a therapist who can help you get from where you are to where you want to be. My practice is committed to helping you achieve your goals in a timely manner. Time is of the essence and you want to do the work and enjoy the results. Join me as we assess what is keeping you stuck where you are, gain resources and skills to use in our work together, and jump in as we process areas that feel stuck in order for you to move into where you want to be.  We will not move faster than you want to go but we will move our way through the therapeutic process in order to get you feeling and functioning better.We will work to create goals for therapy. Session by session, you will be equipped with emotional, thinking and experiencing skills that allow us to process troubling memories and experiences keeping you stuck. As those are being processed, you will grow in your confidence and competency  to get past what's holding you back from achieving your goals.Your life has value. Painful experiences can be transformed into wisdom. I have tools to help you do this so that you can rewrite your story in a way that makes sense and sets you up to thrive moving forward.

I believe that therapy can be a rewarding and life-changing experience. I became a therapist to help people lead happier, more productive lives. Clients need a sense of connection and trust, but also need someone who will gently challenge long-standing beliefs and patterns in a way that leads to positive change. I have been a therapist in the Davis community for 20 years, and have extensive training in Biofeedback, Neurofeedback, Coherence therapy, and Long term psychodynamic psychotherapy.Neuroscience research has demonstrated that conditions such as depression, anxiety, PTSD, ADD, and more have brain signatures that can be seen with brain mapping procedures. Once mapped, using auditory feedback and visual feedback, I can effectively retrain and normalize brainwave signatures resulting in symptom relief and increased well-being.I am particularly interested in Optimal Performance Training. I integrate biofeedback, neurofeedback, and talk therapy to help people perform at their optimal capability. This includes athletics as well as any endeavor which requires high level functioning.

Is something in your life not quite working the way you would like?  Are you feeling stuck?  It can often be helpful to talk though some of the issues we are struggling with in a therapeutic relationship that feels understanding, safe, and compassionate.  Human beings aren't meant to "go it alone".  In fact, feeling alone is inherently traumatizing itself.  I have been licensed for over 20 years, working with individuals, couples, and families to heal their relationships, and to overcome trauma, depression, and addictions.My approach is humanistic, attachment focused, and relational. I don't believe I have the answers to your problems, but can work with you to discover those answers for yourself.  My experience includes working with step-families and LGBT clients.  I have been trained in EMDR and Emotionally Focused Couples Therapy (EFT).I have taught in the University of Phoenix Masters of Counseling program and currently provide supervision and consultation to other therapists.   If you would like to meet to see if we would be a good match, please feel free to give me a call.

The Nexus Station is a health and wellness center for teens and young adults.  We offers 3 different types of programs at Nexus. Each program/therapeutic intervention has been specifically designed to meet a need identified within our community. We offer individual and group therapy, health and wellness workshops and mentor programs. The focus at the Nexus Station is the mind body connection. Every program The Nexus Station offers integrates the mind body system in an intentionally active, playful and relational way. Nothing is left out.

Starting therapy can often bring up many feelings; and taking those first steps to find a good fit between you and your therapist is an important part of the process.  We will work together to create a relationship that feels safe enough to address your concerns.  In addition to my private psychotherapy practice I have provided trauma informed therapy to individuals and families in various community based, non-profit agencies, in addition to Clinical Supervision.My expertise includes struggles with relationships, early childhood trauma, life transitions, gender exploration/affirmation, self-esteem, anxiety, and depression. I have developed a specialization treating complex trauma.  I have been trained psychodynamically and work from a relational perspective, using an eclectic approach that fits with my client needs.I have a special interest in working with Queer and Transgender/Gender variant individuals and families.  I have extensive experience and interested working with youth and their families to help navigate the difficulties and conflicts that arise in adolescence and young adulthood.  I provide support to families navigating gender variance and exploration.

Are you tired of struggling with your mental wellness on your own? We all have ups and downs in our lives. But wouldn't it be great to feel a reassuring undercurrent of serenity and resilience, no matter what is happening in your outer world? What you want is equanimity, and the way to get there is by turning your focus inward, and embodying the courageous leader of your own internal family of mind parts.  Along the way, you will rediscover your innate capacity for awareness, creativity, and compassion.As your therapist, I take the time to research, test, distill, and integrate ancient wisdom with modern neuroscience for treating psychic  and  psycho-physiological imbalances of all types in a sustainable way. Allow me to help you experience the freedom and possibilities of a clear mind.

Hello, my name is Bethany and I believe psychotherapy requires finding the right match. I work with adults, couples, and families with adult children. I utilize treatment modalities that assist with mood, relationship difficulties, loss and grief, parenting challenges, life transitions, codependency, guilt and shame, trauma, addiction, divorce, chronic illness and/or pain, and career stagnation. I've had success with clients who are ready to do the work of self improvement and eager to understand why they may feel stuck. Congratulations on taking the first step toward healing and growth. What are your goals?I'm skilled at guiding people along the journey of change and I partner with you to determine exactly what you want and how to achieve that.  I'm most interested in helping my clients live their best authentic life possible. I'm trained in EMDR, DBT, CBT, Mindfulness, Solution Focused, & Exposure Therapies. I utilize Conscious Loving techniques with couples.I am a strengths based therapist. I provide an affirming, non-judgmental, and culturally competent environment where relief from what's distressing you is possible. I will work with you to develop insight, determine a plan, and reclaim what's been lost. If you think we might be a match, please contact me (916-525-8600). I would love to hear from you.

education.school: Cornell University/Sac State Master of Social Work

paragraph_descriptions: My passion and focus are working with adolescents, children, and families experiencing distress in their relationships. I approach my work with clients from a place of genuine curiosity and understanding. I aim to provide a safe space where we can discuss the challenges getting in the way of achieving your goals and create a sustainable support system for lasting change in your life. I pride myself on being transparent during the process and an active participant in every session.I have extensive experience with adolescents suffering from anxiety, depression, self-esteem issues, self-harm or conflict with peers and family. Additionally, I have spent years in schools providing guidance in the IEP/special education process and helping children of all ages needing assistance to achieve academic success.  I am also trained in EMDR.In addition to being an LCSW with experience working with children and adolescents, I obtained advanced training and certification in Emotionally Focused Therapy (EFT) for work with couples and families. The aim of my EFT is to foster the development of secure and successful relationships between partners and within families.

Some of us who need extra support have a hard time getting to appointments precisely because we are stressed out, ill, or overwhelmed. I travel to bring the support you need straight to the comfort of your home. Individual therapy sessions take place masked or outdoors at your home, as well as via videoconferencing.I believe that personal struggles often arise as a result of harmful internal beliefs, or some factor in our lives not matching up with who we truly are inside. I use compassionate and creative strategies to help you identify the root of the problem, get to know yourself, and bring your life closer in line to the YOU that was there the day you were born!

Are you suffering from anxiety, depression or the aftermath of trauma? Do you struggle with painful patterns in your life that persist despite your best efforts toward change? Are you nervous to try therapy because of the expense and exposure? Have strong effort and promising insights in previous therapy failed to bring you relief? Are you struggling with a difficult child or teenager and feeling like your good intentions and best efforts are not reaching them? Traditional, insight-oriented therapy may help with such challenges--but if not, behavioral therapy may help, regardless of success with mental insight and understanding.Insight may help you quickly, so I will always pursue insight with you. But I specialize where insight stops. I believe that what we do predominantly creates and/or maintains our thoughts and feelings. I use evidence-based techniques (exposure therapy, ACT and CBT) to help you reliably improve your behavior to positively change your thoughts and feelings.My approach works with or without medication, and is designed to minimize your risk by teaching you symptom-reducing skills quickly. I can work with your child/teenager directly, but I may be able to help you with them just by talking with you. I am somewhat technical, but you will find me kind, approachable and non-judgmental. Call for a free consultation.

I provide attachment-based Emotion Focused Therapy to couples and individuals. I commonly work with couples/individuals for over a year, sometimes much longer if the situation requires it. When working with couples, I commonly do a combination of couples meetings and individual meetings.

education.school: Columbia University School of Social Work

paragraph_descriptions: As a therapist, the connection between my client and me is central to the process.  By fostering a safe and deep relationship, we can explore both immediate and historical issues that are causing suffering and pain.  We will use a combination of mind, body and emotional understanding to explore the layers of the self.  With increased insight and awareness, you will feel a greater sense of well being and satisfaction in all areas of your life.My therapeutic approach uses both breath work and yoga therapy to help decrease reactivity, increase emotional understanding and develop a bigger "tool box" of coping skills for managing stress, anxiety and depression.  Whatever your issue, worry or concern, our connection will help you to understand yourself and make the necessary changes in your life.My combination of mind and body awareness works well for many issues, particularly anxiety, depression and eating disorders. I work with individual adults, couples and teenagers to develop a stronger, more stable sense of self, whether you are in an immediate crisis or want to improve your overall well-being and satisfaction.

When you need someone to talk to, when anxiety or depression, move you to call a therapist, I am available to listen and to help. I am a licensed professional, with over 46 years of experience specializing in psychotherapy for individuals, couples and families. People in all phases of life- from young teens to older adults- find my office to be their safe place.My therapeutic approach is empathic, practical and collaborative based on who you are as an individual, your history, current life circumstances, comfort level and presenting problem(s). I will proceed at your pace, listening carefully in order to understand what's working for you and what's not.My goal is to help you confront the challenges you face by finding and making better life choices. I look forward to meeting with you.

With nearly 20 years of clinical experience, I enjoy working with clients of all ages and stages. I  have extensive skills in working with children, teens, adults, families & couples. I treat clients seeking help with: Relationship Distress, Parenting Difficulties, Depression, Anxiety, Trauma & Life Transitions. I have specialized training in the areas of Emotionally Focused Couples Therapy, EMDR, Trauma, Dialectical Behavioral Therapy and Mindfulness. You’ve taken a brave first step in confronting whatever challenges you are currently experiencing. Whether these challenges are big or small, earth shattering or chronic, I’m here to help. Please give me a call to schedule a consultation and see if my services can assist you. I look forward to speaking with you.

I started my career 13 years ago working with children and families in schools and group homes. I have worked in hospice, hospitals and other mental health settings. I have extensive experience with grief, loss and relationship issues. I have lived in several countries, speak three languages and have an understanding of cultural-based mental health.I work with individuals, age 18 and up,  addressing issues of depression, anxiety, relationship issues, acculturation, adaptation, anger, fear, grief and loss. I also work with couples who desire better communication, improved sexual life and those considering divorce. I have a Psychodynamic approach to treatment, and I see patients virtually or in person.

Shame, anxiety, overwhelming stress and relationship difficulties can disrupt our ability to live a mindful and conscious life. Working with adults and adolescents  to promote acceptance, empathy and compassion is my primary interest and the approach I take in therapy.  I also have experience and a passion for working with clients who are struggling with Eating Disorders and body image issues. I feel that the energy between therapist and client is the first step in healing emotional wounds and promoting positive changes.I believe we are all seeking to find our true authentic self and can do this by having the willingness to explore patterns and behaviors that have impacted our lives in both positive and negative ways.I look forward to building a relationship with my clients that can help them calm their mind,honor their self-worth and discover their inner strengths.

Do you seek to better understand yourself, ease suffering, grow to your full potential, both individually and in relationships, and be more present in your life? Then you're in the right place. Many of the things with which we struggle, such as anxiety and depression, are ultimately tied to difficulties in how we relate to ourselves, and perhaps even more so, to others. Because of this, I see our relationship in therapy as the most important factor in helping you achieve your goals. When we feel supported, understood, and compassionately challenged, growth occurs over time at the level of the brain, promoting long-term change.Much of our work together involves helping you increase your awareness, ability to manage, and utilize your feelings in and out of session to live a valued life . This includes helping you connect with what you are experiencing in the present moment more fully and at a deeper level, as well as understanding how your past has come to influence your present.I work with adults 18 years and older, from all backgrounds. I see our work as wholly collaborative, with you as the expert in your own life and experience and myself as a guide to help you move towards the changes you desire. As such, I am flexible in my approach and regularly seek feedback from you about our work. I look forward to hearing from you!

Therapy can be a powerful tool in deepening relationships, moving through pain, tolerating discomfort, and understanding the unknown! My therapeutic work is rooted in guiding clients to realize their own potential. I develop an empathic, therapeutic relationship with my clients to generate self-directed change. By meeting you where you are at, and helping you see parts of yourself that may feel inaccessible, we can move toward you living life the way you want to.I approach your struggles with thoughtful openness and I will offer you skills to help you improve communication with others, deal with stress, become more aware of how your body and your emotions are interconnected, and much more. I also have experience providing sensitive and trauma-informed care to people with PTSD, autism, ADHD, psychosis, etc.It takes a lot of strength to try to find a therapist. I'm here to answer any questions you may have about therapy, especially video therapy. I offer a free consultation and would love to spend a few minutes chatting with you to find out if we are a good fit. The best way to contact me is via email. Please do not hesitate to reach out!

As an experienced therapist I am effective working with young adults, adolescents, couples, and families.  I address and treat a variety of issues including depression, anxiety, anger, abuse, trauma, and relationships. My approach is tailored to each client's particular needs and issues in a relaxed and nonjudgmental environment. I value my clients greatly and rely on them to let me know what their goals are and work collaboratively to facilitate client growth.My specialties include angry or depressed teens that need help navigating the chaos of adolescence and young adults dealing with the stressors of college, work, and relationships.  With relationships, whether couples or parent and child, I am adept at helping build communication between participants setting the foundation for improved connections.

I specialize in helping people improve their relationships to others like a partner or a child, but most especially to one's self. Symptoms such as depression or anxiety, or feelings of shame, can interfere with these connections. Our psyches naturally want to move towards health and growth yet we can get stuck or hopeless that relief is possible. I believe in the value of self-acceptance. Given that many trauma feelings were created in relationship, I believe we need a trusting relationship to heal. If I'm that person for you, I  take that role very seriously and work hard for your hope, needs, healing, and growth.I want to create a safe and nurturing environment for my clients, but also one that is highly productive and effective.  I understand that therapy requires a big investment in time and resources. I utilize the most updated techniques that have been proven by research to be effective. I welcome your hurt around privilege, oppression, sexuality, racism, etc.I'm a former Yolo County Court Clinician and now have fifteen years of experience helping families through divorce and custody challenges. I offer reunification and co-parenting counseling, assessments, and court reporting. If you think I might be a good fit for you, leave me a message for a free 15 minute consultation.

Mental health is a part of living a healthy and happy life. It is closely connected to our emotions and it could affect us physiologically. Please join me to maintain your mental hygiene and begin or continue your journey to happiness. If you feel sad, depressed, worried, anxious, or lonely let us talk. If you need assistance communicating  with your teenage child; just call.I am an Addiction and Relapse prevention specialist. I have a significant experience in the Behavioral Health field since 1991, and have worked with co-occurring disorders for 25+years. I am a Psychologist and a Licensed Advanced Alcohol and Drug Counselor. I have a great deal of experience working with Depression, Anxiety, and Substance Use Disorder.I am very sensitive to culture issues as a result of working in different countries. I am fluent in speaking Arabic, and could assist with the integration into the American Culture.

You are seeking therapy right now because there are changes you want to make. You have probably considered many avenues toward that change and are not sure where to start or how to keep yourself motivated to complete them. That is where I come in. As a professional I listen carefully to your goals, your fears, your values and all the components that go into successful decision making and change. My profession is unique in that I am privileged to hear the backstory of so many people. As I learn from each of my clients successes and challenges, I pass on what I have learned to you.Our work together may involve strategies including talking, homework, resource referrals and other efforts proven to help people heal. It may include working with your doctor or psychiatrist who can prescribe medications. I have over 25 years in working with mental health issues such as depression, anxiety and bipolar disorder.We live in a busy, complex world.  I believe that you know yourself better than anyone else and I am here to help you see what you need to in order to make the changes that you want in your life. You are a whole and complete individual and we all need support sometimes in our lives. You are ready to make a commitment to yourself. I am here to guide you.

Thank you for taking the time to read my page.  I have a private practice downtown Davis and Sacramento focusing on relationships. marriage therapy, non-monogamy,  and sex therapy.  I also offer a collaborative and supportive partnership in addressing relationship trauma, challenges with sex, and sexual trauma.  My practice includes individual therapy, brief and long-term therapy, sex therapy, and Emotionally Focused Therapy for couples. It is my belief you will gain the best results taking what you learn in therapeutic sessions and applying it to your life outside of therapy.I utilize an integrated therapeutic approach of  Sex Therapy, Emotionally Focused Therapy, Trauma Informed Care, Sensate Focus, Dialectical Behavioral Therapy, Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, Acceptance and Commitment TherapyI work primarily with adults. I specialize in couples work, family issues, affairs, polyamory, sex, depression, anxiety, trauma, relationship issues, and LGBTQ+ populations.

I view therapy as a precious investment of your values and vulnerabilities, so I aim to honor that investment with my commitment to your well-being. Through a nonjudgmental, authentic and compassionate stance, I strive to create a safe and collaborative space for you to explore sensitive issues, experiment with new behaviors, and work towards what matters to you.  Whether you'd like to improve the quality of your relationships, health, work or education, or address mental health challenges, such as anxiety, depression, loss, life transition, trauma and addiction, I will wholeheartedly support your efforts in fulfilling these goals.My primary approach, for both individuals and couples of diverse backgrounds, is Acceptance and Commitment Therapy, of which I’m also a trainer for mental health professionals.  ACT is an evidence-based practice that promotes the engagement of one's values along with skills to effectively handle the difficult thoughts and feelings that show up along the way.To best meet your needs or goals and ensure a good fit, I invite you to reach out to introduce yourself and ask questions about my approach and what you can expect from working with me.  I also have specialized training in trauma-based approaches and nutritional psychology.  I genuinely welcome people of all cultural and intersectional diversities.

My work focuses on finding effective strategies to operate in the present then tackling emotional flashbacks and quagmires that keep us tied to past.  Finding a therapist who fits can make all the difference. My clients tell me that they feel safe, seen, and heard with me.  Please call me for a phone consultation to find out if my practice would fit for you.

Today is the day you’ve told yourself, no more, I’m ready to feel better and find relief. Finding the right therapist is essential. That’s why at Three Figs Counseling Center we offer free consultation calls for the client to get to know the therapist, and ensure a good match. Our clinicians are highly skilled and have a wide range of experiences and knowledge to help you.  Whether you are struggling with anxiety, depression, relationship issues, self-esteem, life-transitions, support for parents, LGBTQ+ and so much more, we are here to guide you to a better version of yourself.Imagine a life, where you felt less anxious. Less depressed. Had less conflicts in your relationships. Life-transitions felt more smooth. Parents get the support they need to raise their kids. LGBTQ+ individuals feel safe, heard and seen by therapists who support you to be your true self. We can help you get there.Three Figs Counseling Center offers HIPAA compliant virtual visits on your computer or mobile device. Client portal for easy scheduling, paperwork and connecting with your therapist. Visit us at threefigscounseling.com to book your free 15 minute phone consultation today. Grow into a better version of yourself.

paragraph_descriptions: EMERGE Center for Social and Emotional Learning provides a broad array of social, emotional and psychological support services with a primary focus on adolescents and young adults. EMERGE seeks to better engage young people in their own growth process by offering innovative programs and a diverse group of professionals who are skilled and passionate about working with youth. The years between 12-25 are a period of tremendous growth, angst, excitement and opportunity, where the challenge to emerge is never greater.  Our goal is to facilitate that process. EMERGE provides psychotherapy, counseling, groups, workshops, mentoring, parent support and other activities to help young people reach their full potential. Our theoretical orientation is integrative, collaborative, strength-based and youth-focused. Our staff have specialized training in the needs of adolescents, young adults and family systems.Our vision is a world where young people are valued and afforded the resources they need to grow into healthy, strong and happy adults.  EMERGE embraces diversity, equity and inclusion, and we welcome and appreciate all orientations, genders, colors, sizes, abilities, religions, cultures, family configurations and political beliefs.

Often,for individuals, distilling the complexities of life can be daunting but transformative. Discovering one's aspirations can offer life-changing  insight. I help shape each step so that it matches your particular goals, and dreams.  I hope you will allow me to accompany you on this challenging journey of mindful self- exploration.Regarding relationships, these can range from parental, peer, romantic, etc.I help with relational issues that may have eroded over time. I will listen to you with non-judgmental compassion and offer you practical information and techniques to help you achieve more satisfying relationships, and move forward toward your dreams, goals and life aspirations.My experience includes Anxiety and Stress, (MBCBT), MBSR, Emotional Dysregulation, informed Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT),  Emotional Focused Therapy, Parenting Skills, and Integrative Psychodynamic Therapy. I have worked with individuals of all ages, families, and older adolescents. I have over 25 years experience as a full time university professor and experience with students from UC-Davis.

paragraph_descriptions: Hi! Glad you’re here. I am a Clinical Psychologist licensed in CA where I have grown up and lived my entire life. I provide high quality virtual mental health care / individual therapy and counseling services to adults ages 18 and over throughout California. I specialize in in helping my clients with depression, anxiety, relationship problems and trauma/PTSD. My job is to help you get unstuck and focus on living your best life now. This may require managing difficult feelings, life challenges, and traumatic past experiences like childhood abuse. I love working with all clients of all backgrounds and identities.In addition to my telehealth private practice, I work in an adult outpatient psychiatry department. I specialize in working with clients with anxiety and depression as well as the LGBTQ/queer community and those with other marginalized identities. I employ a supportive, engaging, and collaborative style to empower my clients to reach their full potential.I recognize it can be hard to ask for help. Stigma about mental health can make that harder. I believe every client can succeed, and I think of myself as a fellow traveler on your adventure of self-actualization and growth. I provide an environment of warmth, safety, trust, and always a little humor. Please reach out if you think I might be able to help!

When presented with problems we generally try to solve them as best we can with the tools available to us. Usually we're able to do so. However, sometimes this universal human instinct to problem-solve also creates the conditions of our own misery. In trying to "think positive” or "be happy" or "stop worrying," what we're really looking for is control. Yet the more we cling onto this control, the less effective it becomes over time. Not only do we feel worse than before, our lives become smaller and smaller until we feel trapped in a prison of our own creation.Although traditionally trained in Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT), I primarily use Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT) in my work with clients. ACT employs mindfulness to better understand and learn to accept our desire to control. Only through this awareness are we given the freedom to choose how to live our lives: with intention.I hope I get the opportunity to hear your unique story and support your journey of creating meaning in this chaotic universe we share. If you feel my perspective may be beneficial for what you're currently going through, please reach out to schedule a free initial consultation. I'd also be happy to discuss any additional questions you may have at that time.

I help people turn toward more emotionally satisfying lives by providing a safe, non-judgmental, and compassionate atmosphere that facilitates growth. Do you feel as though you are merely surviving rather than fully living? We often live and act out scripts that are no longer satisfying or, even worse, inhibiting and destructive. I can guide you through a process of self discovery that deepens your capacity to face current challenges and enrich relationships. Whether you are struggling with anxiety, depression, life transitions, identity shifts, addiction, or family crisis, I believe the therapeutic process provides a rich landscape in which to heal.I am convinced that awakening the imagination in the context of therapy helps people create a more authentic and multifaceted self image. The re-imagining of the self opens people to the possibilities inherent in the present moment rather than their clinging to defensive coping patterns that no longer serve them.Our fast paced lifestyles and cultural values of high achievement are often not conducive to self understanding. I draw on my background as a former high school teacher and guidance counselor, to provide a springboard for clients to identify and access their hidden talents, untapped potential, and true  desires.

Are you feeling depleted and overwhelmed? Are you finding it difficult to connect with others or no longer feeling like yourself? I assure you, you are not alone. I am here to help. I have over 15 years of experience providing support to children, adolescents, adults and families struggling with anxiety, depression, interpersonal conflict and self-esteem issues. I really enjoy working with parents. One of my passions is working with people on the autism spectrum who want to build socialization skills that allow them to celebrate the beautiful person they are rather than focus solely on how they conform to societal norms.My therapeutic style is integrative and pulls from different therapy models depending on individual needs. Some of the therapy models I incorporate include: Cognitive Behavior Therapy (CBT), Dialectical Behavior Therapy (DBT), Mindfulness Based Stress Reduction (MBSR), the Gottman Method, compassion focused and client-centered therapy.I approach my work with clients from a place of genuine compassion and patience. I bring a transparent realness to the therapeutic process which I find fosters a healthy, trusting and secure relationship that lends itself to sustainable and positive change. I welcome you to contact me for a free phone consultation to explore whether I might be good fit you.

In my thirty years of practicing psychotherapy, I have found that it is the therapeutic relationship itself which helps effect the greatest changes.  I offer a safe, supportive place to explore the impact of trauma and loss and be able to move on.I try to provide an environment in which clients feel comfortable sharing difficult experiences.  It takes time to build the therapeutic relationship, and I am respectful of where the client is rather than impose an agenda of my own.It takes great courage to seek help and allow oneself to be vulnerable to another.  I offer an experience in which you don’t have to hold on to painful or anxious feelings alone.

Experienced therapist with over 30 years working with individual women, children and parents in teaching, research, & clinical settings. My background in Human & Child Development drives my Humanistic, developmental and whole-person approach. Specialities include fostering healthy attachment, treating trauma and PTSD, anxiety, depression, and supporting families with children with Special Needs.  Modalities include Child-Centered Play Therapy, Attachment-based therapy, EMDR, FLASH, Art,  Sandtray and home-based therapy for children under 5 years of age.Empathy and compassion are cornerstones of my relationships.  I prioritize open and honest communication and collaboration while formulating and working toward client goals.  I appreciate and honor the complexity of each person's unique experience and how it impacts the development of the Self and the dynamic relationships within and beyond the family.Additional services may include psychoeducation, referrals, coaching, 504 and IEP advocacy for students with disabilities.

paragraph_descriptions: Are you in a place in your life where you feel you have lost your voice? I empathize with my clients how it feels to lose their sense of self and to seek direction in life. As your therapist, I want to help you break down your problems and illuminate the parts of yourself that want to be discovered. I help clients that come from diverse cultural backgrounds, life stories, religions, and family traditions. I meet my clients with an endless curiosity and a passion to learn where they derive from. I adapt my therapy style by considering individuals’ generational histories.I work with multicultural individuals and couples who are motivated to work on their relationships and are looking for ways to strengthen their unity despite pressures from their differences. I believe finding your voice as a couple can help overcome societal expectations and connect you even closer.No matter what you have been through, there is an opportunity to create clarity and direction to navigate life’s uncertainties. I will provide a gentle, structured, caring space to free yourself from feeling powerless and to build your confidence. I am here if you are ready to take the next step in your healing.

I believe all human beings move naturally towards self mastery and belonging. Early trauma, developmental hurts, grief and bad luck disturb our wholeness and full potential. We are caught in protective layering of negativity, pain and self defeating behaviors. This state of disconnection with happiness and full embodiment is what brings people into my office. Who am I? I am a deeply empathetic and authentic person. I have a sense of humor. I am inquisitive about my client's journeys. In the rich ground of the therapeutic relationship historical wounding can be reworked and a new sense of self can flourish.I amalgamate techniques of guided imagery, mind/body awareness, active meditation and EMDR. I facilitate the journey towards becoming fully awake and unburdened. The therapy hour becomes filled with possibilities and explorations.

My Goal is to support clients in exploring their past and present to uncover unhealthy patterns that may cause distress and stops them from creating the changes they seek. We will collaborate together to create strategies and solutions based on a holistic, cognitive, and psychodynamic approach that supports you in meeting your personal and professional goals, as well as creating lasting change in your life.My life has been about serving others and continuing to educate myself in many different areas to help people in a more holistic manner that addresses concerns of the mind and body to bring them into better alignment. I have a masters in Mental Health Counseling, a Certificate in Systemic Couple and Family Therapy and in Integrative Nutrition-Health Coach.Counseling is a safe space where you can explore darkness with an understanding person that wants nothing more than to help you reach that infinite power and radiate that light. I can be that person. If any of this speaks to you, please reach out to me so that I can meet you where you are in your journey, and we can continue moving forward together.

Life can be challenging at times. However, I believe that people have an amazing ability to heal and transform negative patterns that are no longer serving them, as well as develop more meaningful ways to approach life's hurdles.  We can often get stuck during difficult moments, and outside support can be helpful during these times. As my client, I will support and encourage you to identify the solutions that are best for your life.  I understand that deciding to reach out for help can be intimidating.  My treatment approach will respect and honor your individual process.I work with a range of clients including adolescents, adults, families, and couples.  I have experience working with clients who are struggling with eating disorders, negative body image, relational conflicts, life transitions, addictions, poor self-esteem, depression and anxiety.I look forward to building a relationship with you and being part of your journey to create a greater sense of well-being and cultivating a more fulfilling and satisfying life! My offices are located in Davis and Vacaville.  If you are in need of a lower fee, I also supervise associate therapists.

My practice focuses on helping people develop healthier relationships with themselves and others. I believe in building a safe, respectful and compassionate relationship with my clients where we can exchange direct, honest, and meaningful feedback. Within this trusting relationship, we can explore your challenges and strengths so that you have more healthy choices regarding your life goals. Whether you struggle with anxiety, depression, stress, anger, isolation, grief or relationship issues, or if you simply want to live more authentically and fully, there is hope. Key elements in the change process include curiosity and a desire to learn about yourself.Because we are all unique, my therapy approach is flexible depending on your needs and goals. I integrate current research and a range of theoretical orientations in my practice (e.g., relational, attachment, neurobiology, mindfulness, and CBT). I work primarily with adults and older adolescents in individual and group psychotherapy.While individual therapy comprises much of my practice, as a Certified Group Psychotherapist, I know the power of group therapy to improve old relational patterns, sometimes in ways that surpass individual counseling. When relevant, this can be a wonderful treatment option. I welcome you to call for a free phone consultation.

Hello fellow community members. I'm so happy to see that you’re taking the time to reinvest in your most important and valuable asset, you! I offer telehealth therapy throughout California while based out of Davis focusing on anxiety, depression, ADHD, life transitions, and grief. My practice includes a tailored approach using brief and long-term therapy using trauma informed care, ACT, CBT, and DBT techniques.I have significant experience working and living within the LGBTQ+ community providing gender affirming care to the Trans and Non-Binary community as well as supportive counseling to their loved ones. Additionally, I work with adults experiencing chronic illness in confronting the struggles that come along with complex, and often life changing, diagnoses.In working with me we can work to identify thoughts, emotions, and triggers to build upon the strengths that you have as the strong competent human that you are.   Whether you are just beginning your journey into mental health wellness or interested in gaining additional skills and strategies to cope with daily stressors, I welcome you.

You know there's more to life than the loneliness, frustration, and fatigue you somehow keep coming back to. Despite the many times you've mustered the strength to push through and keep trying, sometimes you feel like true lasting change is hopeless. But something in you keeps calling, drawing you forward in search of the ease, passion, inspiration, and freedom you're longing for.I believe it's possible for you to get past the stuck places and move into a life that feels abundant and rich with what matters most to you. I can help you put the pieces together in a way that leaves you feeling whole, empowered, and in touch with yourself and your purpose.Our world is full of suffering and injustice, but it is also full of growth and restoration. I can help you expand your capacity for healing and embrace that which is most life-giving to you. I can meet in person in Davis, and I offer Telehealth everywhere in CA. Call me for a free phone consultation - let's see if it's a good fit!

Are you in the process of becoming who you truly want to be? Do you want to know yourself better, and reach deep acceptance of your unique needs, feelings, and experiences? Do you want to be seen and understood by others in a way that makes you proud to be you? Would you like to learn creative and compassionate ways of communicating with yourself and others, including some of the more challenging people in your life? Are old messages and hurts getting in the way? Do you want the freedom that comes from telling your story, leaving behind what doesn't serve you, and deciding on the next chapter?I work from my intuition, and encourage clients to listen more closely to theirs. I employ narrative exercises, music, poetry, art, breath work, guided visualization, and teachings from my yoga practice. Genuine connection brings alive these tools for anxiety and depression symptom management and trauma resolution. I also offer walking therapy sessions. Please reach out and let me know a bit about what you're facing, and get a sense of whether I might be able to support your path to a healthier mind, heart, and body- I practice from the belief these are deeply interconnected.  I strive for attuned, objective, and honest interactions, and would be honored to bear witness to your struggle and your healing.

I am a Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist in private practice for close to 20 years. I am currently seeing individual adults and couples and assist in coping with stressors of work, social and interpersonal relationships.Currently I am very excited to train with AASECT-certified sex therapist Martha Kauppi, MFT, on Assessing and Treating Sex Issues in Psychotherapy, at the Institute for Relational Intimacy.My goal is to provide a safe place for clients to learn about themselves, their connections to others, and their world. I look to empower them to expand their sense of what is possible for their quality of life and relationships.

I believe that psychotherapy is one of the best gifts you can give yourself. Whether you are interested in therapy in order to deal with challenges you have already identified in your life, or you are seeking therapy to connect to yourself, my aim is help you carve out a path and live a more meaningful life. Together we can work closely to deepen your understanding about your struggles and their underlying causes. I can provide you with a safe space to analyze your thought patterns and behaviors while supporting you through the process of making important changes in your life. I enjoy working with children, adolescents and adults. I might be a good fit for you if you would like to  (a) overcome feelings of depression and anxiety, and rediscover satisfaction and meaning in your life.  (b) seek help to effectively navigate life transitions such as beginning of school, a new career or a new relationship...(c) improve your ability to connect with people and work on unhealthy relationship patterns.  (d) process the impact of traumatic events on your life and build adaptive skills to cope with the effect of trauma. (e) deal with identity conflicts or explore issues pertaining to racial, cultural, ethnic identities.

Welcome!  I am accepting new clients.  I offer an environment where my clients feel comfortable, safe, and accepted, needs we all share that when met, enable us to be our best. My belief is that wellness encompasses mind, body, and spirit; it is a constant balance and when scales are tipped, we may not feel like ourselves.I strive to help clients reach their full potential by reinforcing strengths, abilities, and building resiliency. I empower them to be their best selves. My background is working with first responders. I am familiar with the challenges of balancing unique work stressors that can influence all aspects of life.I have experience working with a range of clients and no matter your age or status,  I have found we all share common needs; to be truly heard and accepted.   I would like to hear about you. I am ready to listen.
