paragraph_descriptions: I enjoy working with many types of concerns and challenges, as well as folks with alternative lifestyles and identities.  I have experience working with the Davis community and UCD faculty, staff and students for over 10 years, as well as two years experience working at The Gender Health Center in Sacramento.People who find themselves having relationship conflicts or challenges, and people who are experiencing anxiety or depression may feel free to seek me out for a free brief phone consultation to see if we're a good fit. *Currently seeing clients Sundays and weekdays **If I am out of network for your insurance, I am happy to provide you with a super bill.My therapy style is very supportive and compassionate, while also solution-focused and fostering of self-confidence. While offering skill-building, support and insight, my goal is to help clients work through challenges and feel like they no longer need therapy for their presenting issues.

Somewhere inside, we have a deep sense of knowing. Some of us stand calmly in it. Others catch glimpses. You belong here: in this place, at this time. You deserve to love and be loved fully. You have unique gifts: yours to delight in and share with the world as you will. If you have forgotten, I want to help you remember. I would be honored to guide you on a journey to: move beyond stories that no longer serve you, activate the intuitive knowing within you, love yourself unconditionally, create a life that feeds your spirit, expand into your authentic, powerful self, find your path and the courage to follow it.The environment I create is nurturing, challenging, accepting, and honest. There is room for humor, despair, and mistakes. As our counseling relationship deepens, our interconnection becomes a means of healing and growth. In addition to talk therapy I use art therapy, ritual, meditation, mindfulness, psychodrama, sand tray, and guided visualization.

You've been able to cope with your anxiety but you've noticed lately that it's getting harder to sit through it while you tell yourself it will pass. It's frustrating, you feel lonely and are starting to feel depressed. I help people with anxiety and depression understand the source. Together we will work through your feelings, make positive changes and develop creative ways to enhance your coping tools. During this process you can gain clarity and deepen your self-awareness. I am a Level 3 IFS (Internal Family Systems) therapist and I will use IFS to support you towards self-empowerment and relief.I understand the courage it takes to look at & talk about your experiences. As an IFS therapist, I will use compassion and will provide a safe place for you to delve into your story. We will collaborate to make sense out of the blocks that hinder you from moving forward.  I am open, collaborative & genuine and I deeply enjoy helping people in their path of self-discovery. You can view my website at www.jenniebasarich.com.

I believe strongly in meeting clients where they are at and taking a collaborative approach to meeting the treatment goals of therapy. I know for some, it can be anxiety provoking to seek therapy, and I strive to create an environment that is warm and focused on the issues that matter to the client.I graduated from UC Berkeley with a BA in Sociology, and then went to Oxford University and got my Masters in Evidence Based Social Intervention. I then got my Masters in Clinical Psychology from SF State, and became a Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist in June of 2017.My orientation is psychodynamic, but I also believe that one size does not fit all, that it is important to tailor therapy to the needs of the client. I believe in the power of empathy, and I also provide direct feedback to clients. I have significant experience dealing with trauma.

Instead of looking at therapy as uncomfortable & difficult, consider this… we are our strongest when we have the courage to reveal & repair the most vulnerable aspects of ourselves. This is referred to as reframing, looking at a challenging situation in a new light. Let’s build some positive thinking patterns together. Laughing is also very therapeutic for the brain as it releases endorphins which increases focus, helps us integrate thoughts, & stimulates flexible thinking which are all important components of change & healing.I’m a strength-based therapist and would love the opportunity to hear your story and draw on my experience and expertise in helping you find the best answers for you.Work Experience: CHW Medical Foundation, Bayshore Family Center, Your House South, Sierra Vista Psychiatric Hospital (inpt/outpt)- Dialectical Behavioral Therapy/Art Therapy, Sutter Cancer Center- Bereavement Art Therapy, IEP driven mental health counseling/crisis response- Kings View Counseling, Yolo County Office of Ed, Davis Joint Unified School District.

Therapy is a collaborative process that can help you live a full and authentic life.  While some people think of treatment as a way to address acute and uncomfortable symptoms, it can also be a tool for personal development.  Most humans engage in repetitive and self-defeating behaviors that interfere with emotional freedom and growth. My goal as your collaborator and guide is to help you identify those cycles and explore new ways of being in the world to achieve a joyful and fulfilling life.

Are you looking for a friendly support in order to gain the clarity of your worries, difficulties, values, needs, and goals.  I want to provide accurate understanding and to walk alongside you with your struggles.  You are the expert in your life, not me.  It would be a privilege for me to share your struggles and breakthrough.           I provide talk therapy, play and art therapy.  Some tools I have found being useful are Affect Management Skills Training, Stress management, DBT informed Effective Interpersonal Skills training, EMDR, and Sensorimotor Psychotherapy. I am certified in Trauma-Focused Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (TF-CBT) and EMDR.  I very much appreciate your courage to reach out and look forward to hearing from you.

YOU DON'T NEED MORE TALK - YOU NEED RELIEF. We don't do journaling out loud. Some forms of therapy can be the equivalent to what we call "journaling out loud" where each session is comprised of whatever you feel like sharing about from your week or your past. While this type of process is important to the counseling process and does occur in some amount each week, this isn't the work of therapy that facilitates healing. In our view, you will feel temporary relief from doing this in the same way that you do when journaling or talking to a friend. In counseling jargon we call this "catharsis."RESILIENT RELIEF: Our belief is that sometimes therapists unnecessarily "hold all the secrets" by failing to teach you what they're doing. This leads to lack of confidence in your ability to use those skills outside of session. In truth, the goal of counseling is to finish in months (not years), and (ideally and in most cases) not need to come back. TACKLE TREATMENT-RESISTANT SYMPTOMS: Many times, we have been successful helping people who have been to counseling multiple times before and not felt the relief they were looking for. Part of how we can be effective in these scenarios is by not just focusing on present symptoms, but focusing on the root causes of the symptoms and addressing those.

I provide support to women that are faced with infertility, loss, grief, birth trauma, parenting NICU babies, medically ill children, or children with special needs, perinatal mood & anxiety disorders, adjusting to motherhood, and partner conflicts after becoming parents.I am dedicated to helping women move past the struggles within motherhood.  If you are ready to learn how we can find ways to make life feel calm, create a confident mother, and have you become the best version of yourself as a mom. As a mom, I have a deep understanding of many of these challenges and look forward to helping you get to a better place.Providing telehealth sessions for clients. Easy online scheduling and paperwork, making it simple to find time for therapy in your busy day. Most people think you're doing well in life. They can't see how your past has left you feeling not good enough, full of self-doubt. You take responsibility for everything. You do a lot (and are great at some things), but your self-confidence can crumble instantaneously. You are stressed and anxious one minute, ashamed and depressed the next. You're no stranger to panic attacks, irritability, feeling blah, concentration troubles, or feeling numb. Your body is paying the price as well, with chronic tension, insomnia, high blood pressure, or unexplained physical symptoms. Living this way is exhausting!You want a life that's more flexible and true to you, free from shadows of the past. Talk therapy hasn't quite been the answer, and you're open to new approaches that acknowledge that trauma is stored in the body and is best resolved through body-informed psychotherapy.The next phase of your journey starts now!  If you are ready to give body-informed psychotherapy (Sensorimotor Psychotherapy) a try, you've come to the right place. Please call or visit my website to learn more about how I can help you. LGBT+ and BIPOC Affirming Practice. I am now providing online psychotherapy via Zoom for clients within California.

Regardless of where you are in your journey, participating in therapy can be beneficial in moving toward alleviating distress, or maximizing what is important to you.  I am a licensed clinical social worker with over 26 years of experience working in integrated health care settings, and have seen the myriad ways mental and physical health can affect people at various life stages. My approach is collaborative and integrative, with focus on the therapeutic relationship, because therapy is most effective when you are comfortable and feel valued.My goal is to understand and help you understand what is most important in the context of intersecting identities, while helping identify ways to navigate around the barriers that have prevented you from achieving those goals. Therapy can be a positive experience in which your strengths are recognized in the process.Although I believe the individual experience and life goals are the primary focus of therapy, I work with those living with depression, anxiety, bipolar disorder, grief, gender identity, relational concerns, and adjustment. I have expertise in adult/pediatric oncology, HIV, and individuals living with chronic medical conditions and disabilities.

paragraph_descriptions: People want to be understood.  Everyone wants to feel good yet each day our moods change as life’s circumstances intrude. For most people this kind of change can be hard work. To change yourself, it is helpful to understand how your thoughts, emotions and actions all interact to make up who you are. Real, lasting change is the result of a bunch of small changes that require a shift in thoughts and beliefs.This is where I come in. I listen to your story and help you gain clarity. I use talk, cognitive techniques, support, a positive attitude, emotional reframing, physical awareness, mindfulness, homework, articles that pertain to your issues, and referrals. Together we can help you attain your goals.Understanding emotions and freeing oneself from old negative messages is a journey which takes some work. When we make changes, we take a leap of understanding first and then our emotional being has to catch up so that the head and heart are in sync.   I work with you to uncover negative messages and release them for healing to occur.

Hello, I’m Sage Warren, my pronouns are he/him/his. I was born in Sacramento and raised in Los Angeles.  Educationally, I completed my Bachelor’s in Psychology (UC Davis) and my Master’s in Social Work (Sac State). I provide therapy virtually or in-person in the Sacramento/Davis area.My specialty areas include:  o Self-esteem and confidence building o LGBTQ community-related issues o Alcohol and drug dependency  o Mental health (anxiety, depression, bipolar disorder, PTSD, and other areas)  o Early life trauma o Grief and loss o Parenting challenges, complex custodial dynamics such as guardianship & adoptionI welcome you to reach out to me for a consult. Psychotherapy is one of the best ways to live an examined life, opening doors to a deeper understanding of yourself and to a new way of being in the world.  Mindfully tending to your psychological space, each of our sessions will focus on exploring practical answers to everyday problems, resolving fears and uncertainties, improving your life, and discovering how the psyche responds inwardly to overwhelming life events or when life-shattering events destroy outer meaning altogether.  Even unavoidable and unpleasant experiences can be a source of psychological freedom.With focused attention, we will reflect on whether something is worth doing, and whether the results of an action are likely to be good for you or for the world. Rather than be an unconscious victim, our sessions will help you participate in a process of finding meaning in your suffering, worth in your reality, and greater flexibility in your thinking.Re-formulating awareness of your situation, opening new connections and freeing your imagination, you will discover how to respond most effectively to changes that are always happening. Our therapy can help you navigate the voyage of your life, connect you to the creative unconscious, and provide an optimal mental experience and, even, transformation.

Life can be difficult at times. Something I have learned over the years, through my own experiences, career paths, academics, and family/relationship struggles. Feel free to contact me anytime and we will begin the process.

For most of my clients depression or anxiety is impacting life in a negative way. Sometimes grief causes this disruption; sometimes a history of early life trauma continues to undermine a sense of well-being; sometimes low self-esteem or feelings of being alone are intensifying. One may be struggling and hasn't yet found a way to make sense of why--"something just feels wrong inside of me but others cannot see or understand it."Drawing on training in relational psychology, trauma therapies, griefwork, and mindfulness meditation, I focus on building a genuine relationship, supporting an inquiry that allows you to settle into who you really are. Our work honors what is sensed and felt in the body, and clears pathways for insight.As each person needs something slightly different, we figure out together which practices and what timing fit given the whole of your life. The goal is to understand, reassure, and relax the protective layers so that what is authentic may come into being.

I find it useful to combine your goals for change as well as the aim to get to know yourself better as the foundation for therapy. This has truly been a crazy time!  If you are feeling overwhelmed, confused, lonely, sad, traumatized or any other normal, healthy reaction to crazy times, we totally get it.  It's hard to get traction and make sense of things when nothing makes sense.   You are not alone.    We feel you, we're here for you, we want to help you. Hello and welcome! Thank you very much for your interest in learning more about my practice.  I approach therapy from a strengths-based perspective, and together, our focus would be on helping you access your innate strengths so that you could reach your true potential and live an enriching life full of meaning and happiness. My approach is interactive, client-centered, and compassionate.  I incorporate a solution-focused approach using cognitive-behavioral techniques.  If you are interested in finding support for your son or daughter, I view you as a invaluable partner in this process and would welcome your participation and feedback.I can support you in overcoming a wide range of difficulties, including anxiety, depression, stress management, parental substance abuse, and childhood trauma, among other concerns.  I also specialize in work regarding Asian-American racial/generational identity issues, international acculturation issues, and children diagnosed with hearing impairments.Please feel welcome to visit my website at www.lorienehonda.com for more information about my practice.

Hi! My name is Tiffany. I'm here to help you tackle that anxiety you have about work and productivity.  You know, those feelings that we try to hide about our imposter syndrome, our irritations and guilt that we have about our families, and of course, the endless frustrations that surround our relationship woes. Why do we end up around people that lead us feeling hurt or unacknowledged?  Why do I keep stressing out and lose motivation right when I need it the most? If you've ever found yourself asking these questions then read on. On the surface, “nothings wrong” but you're interested in improving and investing in yourself.I provide a space for you to empower yourself with feelings of confidence, patience, presence, and inner calm. I guide you with compassion, mindfulness tools, and relaxation skills, allowing you to live life as your best self. Wouldn't it be nice to breathe fuller, gain confidence & adapt to the ever changing tidal waves of life?If you're ready for peace, relief, and space to tackle the cycle that keeps you stuck, then I'm the therapist for you. If you're looking for an environment that's completely committed to your wellness, then you've found it. I guide you in support of your self care, offering brief therapy right in the comforts of your home. Reach out today. Let's chat.

Our ideal client appreciates investing in the counseling process and knows its benefits. 	They value ongoing learning and personal growth. They understand a relationship with self, God and others is foundational to functioning well and handling the challenges of life.  Our ideal client agrees to invest their trust in us (because we are trustworthy) and will dive deep to grow and be transformed into the best version of themselves. They know that whether they are ideal or not, they are also broken as human beings and are fully loved and appreciated in the midst of however they are!We understand the courage it takes to reach out in a time of transition, challenge, or distress.  At Community Counseling Associates, you will find compassionate, faith-based, professional therapists trained and specializing in many areas and approaches that will help you to achieve the changes you desire.Sometimes life throws us a curve and we have difficulty coping with death, addictions, adultery, serious illnesses and other life crises. We are also here to help you learn and grow.  Whether you need counseling as an individual, couple, family, or for children we are standing by to help.

I prioritize developing a therapeutic relationship that is founded upon trust, integrity, compassion, and non-judgment. The emphasis is less focused on "pathology" and more on strength, resilience, and developing an optimal worldview. It is my hope to support you to be more content in life, learn new ways to re-engage life and become more empowered to enact your vision of change. It takes tremendous courage to take the first steps toward healing, change, and growth. Thank you for considering working with me to support you on this journey.I have training and experience addressing various mental health concerns that range from depression, anxiety, relational conflict to gender dysphoria. I also have specialized experience working with same-gender-loving, lesbian, gay, bisexual, pansexual, queer individuals, as well as, gender fluid, transgender, non-binary, and other gender-diverse folks.In addition to my background in providing individual and group therapy, I have completed a 200 hour Yoga Teacher Training Program at Niroga Institute. If appropriate and mutually agreed upon, yoga and/or mindfulness meditation can be integrated into psychotherapy treatment.

During the past 30 years of working as a psychotherapist, I have helped people with anxiety, depression, loss, relationship and work issues, and often just a general sense that something isn't right.  As a Jungian and relational therapist, I am empathic, nonjudgemental, nonpatholgizing, and deeply interested in the uniqueness of each human being who comes to me.  Warm and down-to-earth, I enjoy exploring deeper levels of experience but can be practical and provide suggestions and tools when that is what is needed.With post-graduate training in the psychology of women, I love helping women develop trust in themselves, learn to value themselves for who they are, find the courage to do what is best for themselves, and to discover inner strengh and wisdom that they didn't know they had.I also love helping people who were abused or neglected as children to understand the effects of that abuse or neglect, such as overwhelming internal negative messages about themselves, as effects of the abuse, not as truth, and to become an "aman cara" (Gaelic for soul friend) to themselves.

Welcome! If you are feeling overstimulated and overwhelmed by life right now, I see you. If you are feeling confused about who you are amid life transitions or traumatic experiences, you are not alone. When a traumatic event happens, however big or small, we learn to hide parts of ourselves we deem unacceptable or unlovable. When we are faced with a big life change or constant stressors, these parts will pop up and make us feel out of control. It’s hard to trust yourself when there is a war going on in your head, and your body is screaming “danger!” at every turn.I am here to help you explore those parts of you that are longing for attention and care. I believe that your body holds the innate wisdom to bring you back to your truest self. Through IFS and Somatic practices, we will work on helping you feel safe in your body so you can begin to trust yourself and move through your life with confidence.We will be a good fit if you are looking for someone who is warm, friendly, and curious. I would be honored to be a guide on your healing journey, and I look forward to getting to know you!

Are you unable to reach your goals? Do you feel there are some obstacles in the way of your success? I have been in private practice for 20 years helping people to understand and overcome issues resulting from family of origin issues, life's traumas and repetitive thinking patterns that interfere with their goals. I have experience working with individuals, couples and families from many cultures, religions and alternative lifestyles. Not all therapists can work with all people, call or e-mail me today to evaluate if we are a good fit.My specialty area is long term recovery from substance abuse.  The recovery process an amazing spiritual process! I have had the privilege to work with many people who have successfully achieved long term recovery through affect management and have extensive knowledge of the 12-Step programs.In addition to my work with substance abuse, I also enjoy working with couples and families with adolescent and adult children. Lastly, I am the director of The Auburn Davis Center for Dialectical Behavior Therapy, which is an effective treatment for adolescents and adults  with impulse control Issues.

Are you feeling lost or stuck in your career? Do you feel unappreciated or burnt-out? Are you ready for a career change? Want to grow your career? Do you need some career guidance to point you in the right direction? If so, let’s be intentional in career counseling, and make your career intentions a reality! Receive tailored career counseling to help you grow, meet your goals, and make life easier.At Career Intentions, I offer career counseling and resume writing services designed to help you accelerate your career & achieve  your career goals. When you work with me, my goal is to listen, help you gain clarity, define goals, create an action plan, and provide guidance, support, & motivation to help you achieve your career & personal goals.I would love to work with you in your career and life journey, and help you be where you want to be. I invite you to schedule a free 15-min consultation or to contact me via my website, and we wish you all the best in your career and personal development.

I focus on the development of the therapeutic relationship, first and foremost. This can look like: learning about you, prioritizing what you bring to session, and gently encouraging you to work toward your identified goals. I use what comes up in the therapy space as opportunities for relational skill-building, such as focusing on strengths, building self-compassion, learning to identify wants/needs, regulating emotions, and working through conflict. I interweave understandings of sociocultural context to contextualize your experience, and to move the foci of change from what isn't in your control to what is.I specialize working with queer and trans BIPOC folks. Having worked in university counseling for seven+ years, I also have extensive experience working with: life transitions, career, procrastination, emotion regulation, codependency, perfectionism, identity development, privilege and power, and relationships (friends, partner(s), family, coworkers, etc.)If you're struggling with being hard on yourself and others, like you're hitting a wall with trying to change something about yourself or your relationships, I have a wild hunch that, perhaps, there are reasons. And through this growth process, I hope we can learn to understand, accept, and shift what's in your control and allow for what isn't.

You deserve a happy and successful relationship.  Learn to how to repair personal or relationship issues caused by mental health ailments, communication, trust/infidelity, sex, addiction, parenting differences, past trauma (sexual, physical, emotional), and finances.  Discover how to create and maintain mutual understanding and respect.  Love like you matter.  Our diverse staff believe in affirmative and equitable approaches that support clients, regardless to composition, beliefs, or practices.  Call us to learn how we can help, or visit our parent company's website for more information: www.sacramentocouples.org.  HABLA ESPAÑOL.We aim to offer clients outstanding services by providing our staff with ongoing training in proven and cutting-edge theory and practice. We are a nonprofit counseling that offers a sliding scale fee for counseling and free workshops with flexible hours and days to meet most needs and issues.Relationship Results is a program offered by Couples Resource Collective, a Federally recognized 501(c)3 non-profit corporation.

Sunday Availability! Sometimes we reach a season of life that we need a little help navigating, and the good news is that you do not have to do it alone. I wholeheartedly believe, "when needing compassion, we need someone who is deeply rooted, is able to bend and, most of all, embraces us for our strengths and struggles," Brene Brown.  I work with a wide scope of clients who have experienced trauma, abuse, sexual violence and assault, challenges with sports performance/blocks and injury, codependence, academic or performance anxiety and depression.Brainspotting • EMDR • Students • Emergency Responders • Athletes & Equestrians • I have a passion for working with college students and young adults experiencing stress, life transitions, anxiety, relational issues and have specialized experience in vocational/career counseling, & supporting individuals to overcome obstacles surrounding career transitions.Whether you have experienced trauma, struggle with anxiety, depression, abuse, emotional neglect, or challenges surrounding sport performance, my goal is to provide an environment of encouragement, compassion and understanding to help each of my clients attain the growth and changes they want to achieve. I look forward to being a part of your journey!

Our lives here on earth are a creative experience! At times, we need a place to rest and tend to our inner world. I view the therapeutic process as a brave space to access parts of ourselves that we want to grow and transform. My goal in working with you is to provide a supportive environment that will cultivate an increased awareness of your needs, self-compassion and understanding of who you are becoming.As a trained Nature-Based Clinical Therapist,  I am passionate about using a nature inspired modality by weaving together ​mindfulness, movement, eco-psychology, eco-therapy, horticulture therapy, play, creativity, spirituality, trauma informed care, narrative therapy, family systems theory, anti-oppression and anti-racism practice, and ancestral healing. As a black latinx multi-racial person who identifies as non-binary and trans-masculine, I have experience working with all types of people from many different backgrounds.  I work with families, individuals, those in all types of relationships, children and adolescents.  I work with those who need support with anxiety, depression and PTSD.

Do you ever find yourself overthinking situations or experiencing thoughts going so fast it's hard to keep up with them? What about experiencing extreme sadness with a lack of motivation to do anything, even get out of bed? Has there been a time when you felt like crying but you couldn't figure out why? I understand these thoughts and feelings, and together we can work on decreasing feelings of stress, sadness, hopelessness, and isolation, regardless of the situation.We can also work on finding out WHY these feelings continue to happen. Feeling overwhelmed is exhausting, and with my knowledge and skills in treating anxiety, depression, OCD, and substance use/abuse, we can work on this together, so these feelings don't happen as often. I assure you; you will always be heard with empathy and compassion and no judgement.No situation is too big or too small; the focus is learning how to tackle your concerns with confidence. My specialties include anxiety, depression, OCD, substance use/abuse, domestic abuse/violence, and legal concerns, including probation and parole. Together, we can work through anything.

Change can be hard, and life itself can have some challenges. I believe that we all can use some support to find ways to create meaningful change in our lives. As a therapist, I am here to make you feel seen, heard, understood, appreciated, and valued. Mainly, my work is influenced by guiding individuals, couples, and families struggling with difficult life transitions. I also work with clients struggling with depression, anxiety, mood disorders, difficulties with relationships, and individuals who have experienced trauma. My priority is creating a safe, warm and caring environment for my client.My practice is fluid and often includes a more empathetic and non-judgemental approach. My work focuses on understanding, strengthening, and incorporating a space of processing and healing. I also incorporate therapeutic techniques that allow you to increase self-awareness, reframe thought patterns and habits, and create new meaning from old stories.I believe that everyone processes emotions differently,  and we all go at our pace in life. I am here to go at your pace while providing support.

Psychotherapy is a relationship based on trust. In a caring, honest, and non-judgemental environment, I am inspired to work with people who are seeking to heal, and live their best life.  I use an integrated therapeutic approach in my practice which includes addressing the mind, body, and spirit. I have studied spirituality, and alternative healing in addition to many therapeutic modalities.  Self exploration, insight, and utilizing knowledge can create the opportunity for your growth.Everyone is different, so I work with you as an individual.  As we work with the issues that may overwhelm you, you can discover how to attain the goals that have been hard to reach. I am professionally trained in mindfulness techniques, EMDR, somatic therapy, and other therapeutic approaches to address trauma, reduce stress, and improve wellbeing.Deciding to work with a therapist is a very personal decision which requires trust, and a feeling of safety. I encourage you to interview your therapist prior to making a decision. Please contact me to schedule a free 15 minute consultation.

Hey there! My name is DeAnna and I am a LCSW. I approach therapy through a social worker's lense where I see you as a whole person with many moving parts that impact your mental health and well being. My focus and areas of specialty are teens, young adults and family treatment. I make my greatest effort for clients to play an active role, understand and be a part of their treatment from start to finish I have been assisting teens, families and young adults navigate difficult and debilitating mental illnesses. I have been a telehealth therapist since 2020 and also serve patients in a healthcare setting.I like to truly develop an alliance with my clients in order to implement trauma focused treatment most effectively. I have worked with TF-CBT, DBT, Problem Solving Therapy and attachment focused treatment.I am empathetic and caring and I like to discuss what clients' expectations are from treatment in order to ensure I am able to challenge growth at appropriate times. Working with me is a very open and honest conversation and relatable ways to use and adjust tools to fit your individual situation.

There are many paths to healing and change. The journey is an active one and there is success in simply taking the first step, acknowledging a change is needed.  I have worked in mental health services since 1988 and have worked with many different people and issues.  I believe that developing awareness, of emotions, thoughts and behavior, is the starting place and that understanding where we come from, what got us here can be helpful, but changing how we feel today is the best way to have a sense of power.  I specialize in somatic, or a body based approach to treatment of trauma. Please call or email me for a therapy session today.I specialize in working with people with chronic and traumatic stress, anxiety and depression that result from the undischarged life stressors. Focusing on strategies from Somatic Experiencing, developed by Dr. Peter Levine,PhD, I provide active skills to heal the impact of single event and developmental or relational trauma.Have you experienced single event or multiple traumas? Do you experience anxiety, depression or chronic pain from syndromes? Have you experienced developmental trauma, a chaotic childhood or other chronic traumatic stress? I specialize in Somatic Experiencing, an exciting and powerful treatment approach to working with these complex issues.

Any person who is willing to be open, honest, and try to do the hard work that it takes to address their emotions, stories and take the steps needed to move forward in whichever direction they want to take is a person I want to work with. Whether it's working through unhelpful & anxious thoughts, needing someone to listen to their sadness, help them identify their emotions, and/or finding what they believe is good about themselves, I want to help.I listen to your stories, whether they were deep in the past or recent, find your strengths and what core beliefs about yourself and the world you might've taken. Once those are found, you determine which of those beliefs are helpful and which are not. Then we find the tools and skills needed to maintain the story you want to tell about yourself.

As a group, we have served in Sacramento since 2007, offering various counseling services, groups, classes, and workshops. We practice from an ecosystemic perspective, an interconnected whole. As individuals living in the wider world we must interact with each other, attending to the health of our inner life and the health of our personal and public relationships. We must learn how to balance inner and outer peace with inner and outer freedom. As an ecosystem we function as a unit of very dynamic and complex symbiotic relationships. Our health depends on ensuring balance within ourselves and balance in our communities.We approach care holding these principles as key in healing and growth. As such, social justice and advocacy work are part of the delivery of effective care. We are proud to join with our community in celebration and in action on our collective healing journey that will continue to change the entire world!We Honor: Your unique strengths/challenges, while working to enhance life-skills, coping strategies, and interpersonal relationships. We help you remain active in family and community as a function of wellbeing. We Value: Our passion and commitment to your care. Being flexible and creative in our efforts to help you. Integrity in all our interactions.

paragraph_descriptions: I am a Harvard-trained psychologist with over 20 years of experience working with individuals, couples, and families affected by depression, anxiety, trauma, loss, and life's challenges.  My treatment approach is collaborative, interactive, holistic (examining all factors that affect your functioning), and strength-based (identifying your strengths).  I focus on symptom reduction and skills-building to optimize your quality of life.  I will work with you to tailor a treatment plan that meets your specific needs and goals.  I am bilingual in Vietnamese.  My office is located in Midtown and is half a block from the light rail.My treatment modalities include Cognitive Behavioral, EMDR, Mindfulness-Based, Psychodynamic, and Family Therapy.  I have experience working with clients from diverse ethnicities, ages, religions, and sexual orientations.  I also have expertise working with clients dealing with issues of trauma, acculturation, immigration, and cross-cultural relationships.In addition to my private practice, I also teach at UC Davis. I provide clinical supervision, consultation to organizations on diversity, equity, & inclusion issues, and training on mindfulness-based techniques to cultivate well-being and stress reduction. I've also authored multiple publications including the memoir, "The Gifts of Adversity."

I believe we all have a wise woman or wise man inside us who tells us our truth. Most of us have been conditioned to disregard this inner voice. My goal is to ask the questions that enable you to know what is true for you and to provide the support you need to act on this truth.Licensed since 1990, my focus has been helping individuals,marriages and families deal effectively with life's issues. These include parenting,addiction,infidelity,divorce and trauma of all sorts. I have a solid knowledge of mood disorders and work collaboratively with a person's medical professional.I have a particular interest along with extensive training and experience working with families struggling with attachment issues after adopting a traumatized child. Parents say they are grateful to have a therapist who is compassionate and direct, understanding that adoption is the solution; trauma is the problem.

I am Iko Miyaki, MS, MFT. I am orginally from Japan and provide psychotherapy services in both English and Japanese. As I work with my clients, I try to focus on the following aspects:(1) helping my clients increase awareness of how they relate to themselves and others; (2) assisting in developing various skills to improve their relationship with themselves and others.I often utilize experiential interventions, such as Focusing, Ericksonian Hypnotherapy, and Gestalt techniques. It is my professional belief that experiential learning is one of the essential factors for change and growth.

Hi there, I'm Andrea.  Have you been feeling stressed and overwhelmed? Have changes or new challenges in your life evoked feelings or thought streams difficult to manage? Does it feel harder to know how to communicate what you need or feel supported by someone in your life? My goal in working with you is to develop trust and connection; to team with you so that we can identify what is not working and build skills so that you can feel more satisfied in your life.  I have over 20 years experience working with adults, couples, adolescents and families.My approach is collaborative and individualized to meet your specific needs for support. Together, we will utilize your strengths and practice new ways to manage stress, emotional difficulties, and the challenges life can bring. I have decades of experience helping clients with anxiety, mood issues, trauma, relationship problems and major life changes.I am straightforward and I want you to feel empowered and confident to enact the changes you seek. I want you to feel that the therapy process can be productive and helpful. You are not alone!

I work with children, adolescents, parents, couples, and families. I am warm, real, and collaborative. If you and/or your family members choose to work with me, I'll endeavor to create an environment that feels safe enough for you to take risks, be authentic and make lasting changes. We'll work together to explore the dynamics that may inadvertently by contributing to a problem cycle, so that you can feel empowered to act in more preferred ways of being.I specialize in attachment-based approaches to child, family, and couples therapy. I have received specialized training in a form of couples therapy called Emotionally Focused Couples Therapy (EFT). I am also a Mindful Self-Compassion teacher and mindfulness guides my presence in therapy and how I think about change.As a parent, I know from the inside out how challenging parenting can be and the strain a new baby can place on a marriage. I am passionate about my work with couples and families and I also provide training to schools in brain-wise, attachment-based approaches to discipline.

I work with individuals and couples who are committed to creating more satisfying relationships through a better understanding of their partners and/or who are struggling with fertility. I also have a special emphasis on working with People of Color.We may be a good match if you...  Struggle to feel important in your life, especially in your relationships, or feel like you and your partner just can't get on the same page anymore. Or maybe you are on a fertility journey and could use some help rediscovering your purpose and joy in the process.You may also be thinking that some of your struggles are the result of your parents or grandparents' choices and would like to change that to be a better partner or parent. You don't have to do it alone! My job is to help you find the answers and joy you are looking for. I look forward to working with you!

Professional and affordable counseling for individuals, couples and families . . . Your life counts, and when times are hard, you owe it to yourself to take constructive action. You may find the most valuable action will be your decision to pursue counseling. I offer a telephone consultation at no cost to help you with that decision.  In addition, I offer expertise in helping individuals and couples who are experiencing reproductive loss, such as infertility and miscarriage.I work with clients to improve life satisfaction and reconnect relationships by not only working on "what's wrong," but also by building on what is strong. 

With respect to my work with couples, I have advanced training in Emotionally Focused Therapy (EFT), a proven effective method.As a licensed clinician, I can provide you with the commitment and professional expertise you deserve.

My goal is to help you feel less alone and overwhelmed by the challenges life can present. Whether it's panic attacks, social anxiety, sadness, apathy, lack of motivation, anger, relationship conflict, or other concerns, we'll work on a solution. I understand how limiting psychological distress can be and am passionate about helping you start living a more meaningful and engaged life.                                    I draw from the insights of psychodynamic theorists to explore unconscious motivations, from the wisdom of interpersonal thinkers to understand your relationships, and from the science of cognitive behavioral researchers to change your thinking and attitudes.

How would you like to live a vital, fulfilling life and reduce the effects of stress and anxiety that keep you stuck? I offer integrative mind/body approaches to health and wellness, including ACT and Mindfulness-based psychotherapy, Somatic Experiencing, a tailored use of meditation and body awareness techniques, suggestions for lifestyle adjustments, and emphasis on Being in the moment.  I am also interested in existential issues like aging, transitions and losses, relationships/communication problems, and managing changes. Being mother tongue Italian, I am happy to offer bilingual services to Italian-speaking clients.My professional experience is broad, and includes working with people suffering from anxiety, depression, sexual and physical abuse; adult children of alcoholics,  war veterans, college students, women, families, couples, adults and adolescents. I can guide towards clarification of your life values and challenges, and towards  fulfilling life changes.I believe that everyone can get better and start healing, no matter what life situation one is experiencing. I will provide you with the safe environment, tools, support and guidance needed to grow and enjoy a fuller life. By accepting what is, the first step is taken toward constructive change.

I am dually licensed as an MFT and a Psychologist.  I am also a hypnotherapist.   I treat many conditions.  Depression, Anxiety and PTSD for example. I believe that the therapeutic connection is essential;  I respect my youngers as well as my elders.  However, I believe that what differentiates a psychotherapist from a paid friend is a mastery of the unconcious.  I therefore include in my practice methods that tap into a person's inner knowledge of self: EMDR, Natural Processing, hypnosis, inner child work and Gestalt dreamwork.  I see the unconcious as the last frontier, and we are pioneers!If a person is not motivated to overturn their psychic rocks, I can use hypnosis to increase relaxation and improve functioning in a more direct manner.
Persons seeking to purge a past trauma are well served by EMDR.  
Persons not sure can often find their way with Gestalt dreamwork.I was given the Patients' Choice award for my Woodland practice in 2016, by Opencare.    My clients love my sense of humor. Many of my clients get more out of therapy than they expected to.   Featured in Laurie Cole Johnson's  book Finally Winning.  Fluent in Spanish.  De veras!

I have been providing and managing behavioral health care services in the Sacramento Metropolitan area since 2000.  I am a professionally trained therapist whose goal is to help individuals, couples, and families face their emotional issues with courage and strength while learning to grow and change in a motivating and safe environment. I use multiple treatment modalities which draw upon the personal strengths of my clientele.  In addition to English, I speak Gujarati and Hindi, and am comfortable working with people from many cultured and backgrounds.I have extensive training in helping individuals process their past traumas  using a cognitive behavioral approach.My practice is conveniently located in downtown, close to major freeways, within walking distance of the Capitol, and next to ample parking.

You are committed to feeling better, you've tried everything, but still you feel lost in the pain. You've always been able to "fix" things in your life, why not this?  This time, you feel stuck. Maybe you feel gripped by anxiety or panic. Maybe you feel consumed by grief from trauma or loss of a person, pet, or life dream. Maybe you're finding yourself in new life circumstances (a significant health challenge, life milestone, career or relationship change) and wonder "who am I now"? Life has a way of challenging us. There is a way through.I specialize in helping people move through the challenges of anxiety, grief/loss, and life transitions. Your own voice holds the wisdom to your healing. I offer a mind-body oriented approach, including EMDR, Brainspotting, and mindful-somatic awareness to help you rediscover that voice and learn to listen and trust it again.My approach provides a compassionate, nonjudgmental space, the conditions I believe we all need to heal and flourish. You are making a skillful decision for yourself by seeking help. Schedule a free phone consultation, through my website or phone, and let's explore how to help you find your way.

If you are feeling sad, anxious, or simply unhappy, you are definitely not alone. My philosophy is that people do the best they can with what they have, but sometimes anxiety, stress, grief, depression and relationship issues can contribute to our feeling stuck. My genuine belief is that change is always possible and begins with being motivated to do something different. My approach is both collaborative and supportive and will help you explore the changes you'd like to make in order to live a more meaningful and purposeful life.My treatment approach incorporates mindfulness to help people cope with the debilitating symptoms of anxiety and depression.  I also utilize EMDR as an adjunct for individuals who have experienced trauma. In addition, I have a particular interest in working with couples and have specialized training in EFT (Emotionally Focused Therapy).

I work with people who are struggling, and decide take the courageous step to ask for help. Many have a history of trauma and suffer from anxiety, depression, eating disorders, addiction, parenting challenges, sleep issues, sexual difficulties, chronic pain, relationship problems, and other post-traumatic responses. Also, present-day situations in our personal or collective worlds can be objectively hard to bear. Our experiences leave traces psychologically and somatically, so I use evidence-based, body-oriented, mindfulness techniques to address limiting patterns so that you can live more authentically today's challenging world.My clients describe me as calm, kind, and real. I appreciate the role of humor, and I am not afraid to gently and directly challenge you when it is useful. We will collaborate, working together on your goals as a team, to help you make the changes you want in your life. Meanwhile, we will celebrate and honor your willingness to engage in this valuable work.I graduated from University of Michigan, attended California Institute of Integral Studies and JFK University, and received my graduate degree in Somatic Psychotherapy from JFK. I have training in Sensorimotor Psychotherapy, Acceptance and Commitment Therapy, EMDR, Clinical Hypnosis, and earned a Certificate in Complex Trauma and Dissociation from ISSTD.

Hi there, I am Donna  I love a mixture of different approaches to therapy to get to the root of what has been difficult or confusing at times during our journey in life.  the ups and downs in our journey in relationships, job stress, and family interactions can be overwhelming and stressful, learning balance is part of what I believe is finding ourselves and identifying the needs versus the wants of life choices and understanding ourselves.I love the empowering of the self.  Working together using a whole self approach addresses what I identify as balance - body, mind, and soul (content or peace) that helps develop a strong relationship with yourself.  Seeking therapy can be a scary adventure, but well worth it.I am transparent, open, and honest with each person I come in contact with, I am here to help you on your journey with mindfulness, understanding, and evidence-based techniques.

Do you want to bring more peace into your life, strengthen your relationships, and increase your joy?  I would love to work with you!  By integrating healthy principles of mind, body, and spirit, I can help you rediscover and develop your core strengths. You will learn new tools to help heal emotional pain, communicate more effectively, decrease your stress, and increase your life enjoyment.
You are worthy of unconditional love and acceptance.  You hold unique gifts to share with the world, and these same gifts can be used for self-healing.  Let's discover your gifts together!I have a special interest, experience, and training working with couples and relationships,  including sexual issues.   I  have hospice experience and training in grief and loss, chronic illness and care-giving.  Other specialties include divorce and remarriage,  blended families, parenting, adolescents, career transitions, and spiritual issues.  LBGTQ ally.I have many years experience as a credentialed science, health, and sexuality teacher. I use proven therapeutic techniques while remaining open to each person's unique experience to find the best solutions for each client.  I use nature, humor, and the client's own spirituality as resources for healing.  I use  cognitive behavioral and psychodynamic methods.

Hello... I would welcome talking with you in person or on the phone about what you are looking for and what I think I might be able to offer you.  Together, we'd  decide about the goodness of our fit. In my practice I work mainly with adults in individual or couple therapy as well as with psychotherapists who want consultation, particularly consultation that incorporates their personal psychological work. I bring 25+ years of experience to the practice of psychotherapy and continue to feel grown and deepened by this process.Deeply interested in people,  I respect the courage it takes to seek this work whether on a long or short-term basis and have a patient trust in this process as a means of learning and healing.  My initial training was grounded in psychodynamic theory which still shapes my thinking.However, how I work is informed by various approaches and crafted to the person. Relationship difficulties can preoccupy one's life. My clients find themselves stuck in repetitive negative communication patterns, they have experienced a recent injury to their emotional bond or fear that the trust in their partner has been broken. Sometimes they repeatedly reach out for emotional connection with their partner, only to end up in the same old disconnecting cycle that leaves them feeling alone and demoralized. paragraph_descriptions: I specialize in the treatment of all anxiety-related disorders, including OCD, Social Anxiety, and Avoidant/Restrictive Food Intake.  After developing a treatment protocol at the Intensive Program level that was the first in the nation to integrate mindfulness-based Acceptance and Commitment Therapy ("ACT") with Exposure Therapy in the treatment of OCD, I am continuing that work in private practice.  My focus is on helping people respond differently to the physical sensations of anxiety, get some space from "sticky" thoughts, and to return to the present moment.Before beginning any kind of exposure to anxiety-producing situations, we will lay a foundation for experiencing the anxiety differently.  People report that it's much easier to approach anxious situations this foundation in place.  We will then refine these skills as you encounter different situations.People often find talk therapy to be ineffective for OCD.  CBT is a common alternative but can be problematic because the goal of changing dysfunctional thoughts to functional ones if often experienced as similar to the battle with thoughts that already goes on in people's minds.

As an ally in the healing process I am committed to honoring your uniqueness. Your experiences, emotions and perspectives are uniquely personal to you - and so are your solutions. By focusing on your strengths and inspirations I help you discover, use and "own" the parts of yourself that are most authentic.  Whether you come to therapy seeking relief from identifiable pain or distress, or whether you come to discover something new about yourself, I believe that something in you already knows what you need. I can help you recognize and connect to this innately wise part of you.I work with individuals who want help opening and trusting - both themselves and others. Many of my clients have a history of abuse or neglect which can cause "stuckness", anxiety and fear of moving forward in their lives and relationships. I help clients heal the past so they can focus on the now.My approach is affirming and interactive. I provide attunement, concrete tools, direct feedback and a range of therapeutic modalities. Through our work together, we will open and tap into the flow of emotional health and aspiration that leads to experiences of peace, clarity, and freedom in your life.

Are you looking for inner peace, deeper meaning, or a more intimate connection to your self and others (your child, partner, peers, relatives)?  If unresolved issues are impacting your life I provide a safe environment to explore and confront the things that are holding you back.  I can help you gain a new perspective to resolve your specific life challenges.I work with clients of all ages.  I have a special interest in working with children, utilizing their natural language of play, to explore unconscious or hidden factors that drive behavior.  Sandplay, art, and bibliotherapy are among the tools I use to facilitate communication and the self-actualization process.My approach is eclectic and flexible acknowledging the uniqueness of each person and their specific needs.  I would be honored to join with you on your journey to health and wholeness.  Finding the right therapist is critical; a complimentary consultation may help you decide if we are a suitable match.

Each of us deserve to lead a happy and healthy life. Yet life's challenges can be overwhelming and seem unresolvable. I provide non-judgmental feed-back to help you clarify those challenges, your goals, options and your own inner strengths. Knowing our strengths and making our own choices are steps toward the life we want. My experience includes trauma (such as sexual abuse and other issues specific to Post Traumatic Stress Disorder), victims of domestic abuse and/or violence, mood disorders, depression, alcohol and drug issues and those with dual diagnoses.I work with all ages and especially enjoy working with children and adolescents. I've worked as a Certified Alcohol and Drug Counselor and Registered Associate Clinical Social Worker for fourteen years. Along with doing effective office therapy since 2001, I've seen tremendous individual progress using Equine Assisted Psychotherapy.EAP is an experiential therapy that can aid people in working through personal issues, feelings and behaviors in a concrete manner by interacting with horses in a variety of activities. I'm honored to work with Kim Jones, MFT, and my beautiful four legged partners, my horses.

I have 20 years of experience specializing in identifying the cause of learning struggles.  I provide screenings and full evaluations for Dyslexia, Dyscalculia, Dysgraphia, and all other educational disabilities, including Autism and Intellectual disabilities.   Follow up counseling can also be provided to help clients maximize their learning potential and understand their own strengths and weaknesses.  With this understanding comes hope and the relief of knowing how to advocate for appropriate accommodations and services in school and college. Knowing how to navigate school resources can be intimidating.  I understand educational systems and can help you advocate for your child's needs.  My approach is always non-adversarial and solution focused.  Results can be used in IEP, 504, SAT/ACT, and College accommodation planning.

Is anxiety getting in your way of you leading your best life? Is something that happened in your life years or even decades ago still impacting you and you don't know how to move past it? Are experiences from your past impacting your relationships? Your work? Your ability to be your best self? Do you have physical symptoms that don't seem to have a medical cause but cause you difficulty in your life? Are you experiencing unexplained panic symptoms? Therapy can help. My work focuses on healing past traumas to help you get your life back. I utilize a two pronged approach. 1) I will help you build skills to cope with current symptoms through mindfulness, guided imagery,  and cognitive behavioral skills.  2) I utilize evidence based practices including EMDR (Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing), and Attachment Focused therapy to help address the core reasons for the symptoms. Reaching out for help is the first step towards feeling better! Please feel free to call or email me to schedule a free phone consultation. We can discuss your goals for therapy, and talk about my practice style to see if it might be a good fit for your current needs.

I am a licensed clinical psychologist who as a generalist works with a variety of presenting problems and enjoys working with different populations. I have extensive experience working with women, men, adolescents, and children with eating disorders and OCD. It is critical to individually tailor treatment to each client's needs. I utilize relational, psychodynamic, cognitive behavioral, values based therapies in my practice. I have experience working with individuals, couples, families, and groups. I have a collaborative approach where therapist and client work as a team to better understand the problem and work towards healing and emotional health.I have worked in all levels of eating disorder care (residential, partial hospitalization, intensive outpatient, colleges) to help those suffering from Anorexia, Bulimia, and Binge Eating Disorder. I also specialize in  treating Anxiety Disorders(OCD, Social, Panic Disorder) and utilize Exposure with Response Prevention.I welcome a diverse clientele and have specialized training with LGBTQ community and really enjoy working with this population. I enjoy working to empower my clients and look forward to working together to develop lasting change in both relationships and with the self.

paragraph_descriptions: Through a respectful process of listening and questions, I work with you to help clarify your goals and values. I will help you find new perspectives and restore a healthy narrative that does not include feelings of blame or shame. We will work together to develop better skills at managing difficult emotions, such as sadness, disappointment, pain, and anger. We will learn to nurture feelings that are healthy and not those that can get us stuck. I hope to work with you to discover a sense of self-compassion and flexibility.My approach includes an integration of guidance, exploration, & problem-solving. My communication is often direct and I use humor in our sessions. I will help you create greater awareness of yourself and improve your quality of life by adapting to difficulties with increased competence.If you are willing to work hard to create lasting change in your life and are interested in creating meaning in your life, I welcome you to contact me. I look forward to building a relationship with you, helping you rediscover your strengths, and securing self-acceptance without self-judgment.

I will work with you to guide you through your depression, grief, anxiety, relationship or spiritual issues to find harmony, comfort, health and balance. I work with an integrative approach. The outcome of therapy is usually greater self-knowledge, a re-integration of de-pressed thoughts, emotions, and beliefs, and a new relationship with self, others, and the world.  Therapy often involves structured "talk" therapy, creative work, an exploration of your dreams, religious experiences, and personal myths.In our hectic life styles we are often told to “just get over it” without taking time to nurture what needs to heal. I work with depression, anxiety, grief, relationship issues (pre-marriage, separation and divorce) and spiritual issues to guide you toward a more satisfying and authentic life.My approach to psychotherapy is guided by the work of C.G. Jung and others who believe that healing is never a temporary fix but an unfolding process meant to bring lasting health and happiness. Psychotherapy is an opportuniy to work toward experiencing yourself more fully.

I believe that we all have an innate desire to become the best person that we can be and we all adjust to difficulties in life in ways that work in the moment but which frequently then become routinized and prevent us from being fully alive and authentic.  I work with people to help them sort through what is not working in their lives and help them access deep internal resources so that they are able to experience greater freedom and choice in their lives.I work with adults and couples.  I utilize a variety of therapeutic modalities including existential, humanistic, transpersonal, systems, psychodynamic and object relations.  I also utilize principles synthesized from Asian philosophy and aikido. However, the most important aspect of all of this is the ability to develop an authentic relationship with my clients.

I am a psychotherapist geographically located in Sacramento, California. Currently, I am only conducting HIPAA-compliant telehealth; if you live outside California, please contact me to discuss options. I have been an independent Licensed Clinical Social Worker for over 18 years, and more generally been a social worker for over 25 years, conducting education, research, supervision, and clinical work. I work with people living with chronic health and mental health conditions, with those struggling with their identity and making meaning in life, and with adults having un/expected challenges in relationships, work, and beyond.My services can range from short-term problem solving and education, to supportive behavior change, to more in-depth psychotherapy. I employ a critical stance, meaning I see our individual existences in active relationship with our environment, communities, histories, cultures, and society. Please see my practice website for more detailed information.In addition to private practice, I supervise non-licensed clinicians, I am a tenured professor of social work, as well as I am the Director/Chair of an accredited school of social work, and I conduct and publish critical health research.

I have worked as a psychotherapist for over 20 years. I meet you where you are, attending to the particular needs and goals you bring, helping you discover more meaning, wholeness, and pleasure in your life. The daily choices we make are often informed by our early life experiences. Despite our best efforts to change, we often find ourselves repeating unwanted patterns over and over.  As we sit together, exploring your feelings, your stories, and listening to your dreams and longings,  we will find ways you can open yourself up to the possibility of change, finding new energy and meaning.We can help you to explore yourself, your relationships, & your direction in life. When you become more aware of patterns and narratives that have shaped you, you will develop the tools & resources necessary to feel better, act, & live a more satisfying life. Whether you're experiencing distress, struggling with a transition, or simply wanting to grow.My practice is designed to help you develop the skills you need to become more resilient to the pressures & stressors of life & to live a meaningful authentic life, striving towards wholeness. When we become more aware, we open to life, & we can meet challenges with more presence &  groundedness. Together we will work towards nurturing who you uniquely are.

I am currently accepting new online/phone clients on Monday and Wednesday. "You may not control all the events that happen to you, but you can decide no to be reduced by them." Maya Angelou. I provide you with a safe place without judgement, together we will find solutions to help you get to a better functioning. I am passionate about the work that I do and I want you to leave my office feeling a sense of tranquility and motivation. As a therapist with a warm, relational style and a commitment to compassionate evidence-based interventions, my goal is to help you discover your true potential.  By applying mindfulness and insight-based therapies, we can develop understanding into unworkable behavior patterns and unhelpful thoughts that may be holding you back from experiencing a meaningful and fulfilling life.  Together, we will help you to create a life that is in alignment with what's most important to you. I offer both long term and solution-focused short term therapy depending on your needs.  I am committed to working towards your goals in therapy and empowering you to create a life guided by your values."And the day came when the risk to remain tight in a bud was more painful than the risk it took to blossom"  --Anais Nin

Are you tired of continually trying to control, change, get rid of, or avoid painful thoughts, feelings, sensations and experiences? If so, together we will explore ways to move beyond these temporary relief strategies towards relating and responding in a more flexible manner. Discover, express and integrate previously unknown parts of yourself, build upon strengths already in place, and work on the past by increasing the vitality of your work on relationships in the present. I am committed to practices that consciously cultivate awareness, acceptance, and encourage a more authentic and vital relationship with self, other, and the world.
