Being a part of the military can add a complicated layer to life and especially to family life. Not only does the military bring its own culture and obligations, it also brings its own "family" component that can get "tangled" when interwoven. Often times service members and partners find themselves struggling to balance family life with work and military life and when life is out of balance a multitude of issues can arise such as depression and anxiety, not to mention coping with any added stress such as combat experiences or other trauma within or out of the military.I specialize in therapy for service members (both current and prior) and their families. Often times service members and family struggle with similar issues as civilians such as: anxiety, depression, substance abuse, PTSD, marital discord, relational dissatisfaction, lack of motivation, etc. except military service can complicate matters further.Being part of a military family has allowed me the privilege of gaining inside understanding and perspective of just how challenging military service can be and the impact it can have on the service member and the family.

I believe our mutual job is to work together to help you find the best ways of dealing effectively with your problem. Sometimes, although we may know the answers to our problems, we have never been taught the skills to implement that knowledge. Part of my job is to use my expertise and education to teach those skills. For example, we may realize we are being misunderstood by others and work hard to be understood, but no matter how hard we try, nothing changes. Teaching communication skills is one of my areas of expertise that may prove useful.My theoretical approach is eclectic, meaning I do not hold to one specific theory  but use a variety of approaches in my therapy. These include psychodynamic therapy,  Rogerian (Person Centered) therapy, Cognitive/Behavioral therapy, and Hypnotherapy as well as a variety  of other techniques, depending on the  situation we are working with.I am a retired law enforcement officer and a Vietnam Veteran.

We all endure challenges at some point or another in our lives yet we continue to strive and move forward to find peace, solace, content, or happiness. Therapy can help identify those goals, overcome barriers, and henceforth, head toward betterment or enrichment via personal growth.I incorporate an authentic, innovative, collaborative, and a solution -focused approach in my work. My approach is drawn from both classic and contemporary evidence-based theories including attachment, relational, psychodynamic, humanistic-existential, systems, cognitive behavior, & dialectical behavior therapy.I specialize in working with children, adolescents, adults, and families who struggle with life issues like, school, family, relationships, sexual orientation, occupation, and stages of life causing stress, fear, anxiety, depression, poor self esteem, anger, or trauma. I also offer parent coaching and conjoint therapy. I conduct functional behavior assessments, offer appropriate referrals and resources.

I have been a psychologist for 45 years.  I earned a B.A. in psychology from Northwestern University in 1967 and a Ph.D. in clinical psychology  at the University of Colorado in 1972.  I taught, conducted  research and treated patients at Vanderbilt University, where I collaborated with Dr. Hans Strupp,  a pioneer in the study of the effectiveness of psychotherapy.  I  published over 100 scientific articles on the process and outcome of therapy and the influence of sex and race biases in diagnosis and treatment.In 1975, I moved to the Department of Psychiatry at the University of California at Davis, where I continued teaching and seeing patients and served as the Director of Doctoral Training in Clinical Psychology.  Since 2011, I have been in the private practice of individual and couples therapy.

Hello and welcome! If you'd like to feel more hopeful, connected, and calm I would love to work with you! I specialize in treating depression, trauma, anxiety, stress, self-esteem issues, body image issues, and perfectionism. I use a person-centered approach and mindfulness to help create a safe space for you to reflect on your relationship patterns and goals. I also like to infuse behavioral therapy techniques to help you hone in on concrete steps you can take to make active changes in your life. I hope to help you find more meaning, creativity, and joy in life.I have 10 years of varied experience in mental health, including teaching graduate school classes, writing a workbook on working through anxiety and worry, and supervising other clinicians toward licensure. I am trained in CBT, DBT, IFS, and EFT and certified in Brainspotting, which is similar to EMDR, and often used for trauma work and performance.Ultimately, I believe that the best therapy happens when clients feel valued and connected in the therapy room.  For more information about me and my services please visit my website at: janeteixeira.com. Initial consultations are free so reach out today! I look forward to meeting you!

Are you looking to improve your relationships, address a particular problem, or move toward your own potential? 

My approach is collaborative, strengths- based, and focuses on you developing both insight and skills to address your problem. I am passionate about helping individual adults and couples get closer to achieving their own potential and move through difficulties. My experience includes, and preference is to work with people of diverse cultural backgrounds, experiences, and sexual orientations. I tend to integrate cognitive behavioral and dialectical behavioral therapy, among other methods. 

I look forward to working with you.I am trained at Level 2 for Gottman Therapy with Couples.

I have been in clinical practice for 25 years. I have been able to work with people from all walks of life who may be struggling with issues that may either be long-standing or contemporary in nature. Therapy begins with trying to help my clients arrive at clearer conceptualizations as to why they are struggling. The reasons behind the struggle may based in history and/or based on a present challenge. My view is that when one has a more accurate view of the issue, solutions, with  therapeutic guidance, tend to follow more naturally.I am first and foremost a clinical psychologist both in terms of training and experience. Over the years I have developed subspecialties in psychological assessment and couples therapy.  I  also work as a sports psychologist with athletes, professional and otherwise, who are looking to enhance their performance, focus and concentration.

My hope is that you leave therapy with a new sense of vitality, feeling empowered with a sense of congruency. I want you have an increased awareness and understanding about yourself and feel more interpersonally connected. I will strive to know who you are and how you see the world while we collaborate and work toward healing. We will focus on your emotional experience, honor your multiple identities, be in the moment, learn new skills, and help you "sit in the struggle."   Therapy is a brave endeavor, and I will do my best to support this journey.Together we will focus on symptom reduction and meaning making, in the context of a strong therapeutic relationship where you feel safe to be vulnerable. My multicultural frame emphasizes understanding individuals within their particular cultural context in which they live, which is often impacted by several historical, sociopolitical, and economic factors.I utilize a variety of strategies as I work with adolescents, adults, and couples. I work with a wide range of concerns and have particular interest in working with depression, stress, major life transitions, relationship struggles, multicultural concerns, self-esteem issues, identity development, grief/loss, trauma, and intergenerational trauma.

Anxiety, depression, grief, loss, and ruptures in relationships are among the many issues that rob us of our happiness and well-being. I have over 15 years of experience working with children, adolescents and adults in therapy. I see therapy as a sacred space to work through the underlying issues that keep us stuck in our suffering. I deeply enjoy working along side individuals and families as they come to find healing from old wounds and a better sense of identity, peace, happiness and fulfillment. I especially enjoy working with college students, adults and couples. Anxiety and depression effect many people and can take specific support to overcome. Many factors cause anxiety and depression. Often developmental transitions (going to college), family history, or current painful losses or relationships can trigger these reactions. I am comfortable working with the many factors that create symptoms.Among the most dynamic and often stressful time periods of life are during developmental transitions. I am passionate about working with young adults/college students through those transitions. Often during transitions at any stage, relationships change or end, new symptoms arise, and discomfort increases. I enjoy working with people through these changes.

With 40 years of experience as a psychotherapist, my style is warm, compassionate and highly focused. I lean on a Developmental framework in nearly every area of your life: some areas are highly developed, others underdeveloped. I work with a traditional social work Strengths Based perspective, which means that I look for what you do well, and how you have successfully coped in the past. With a Cognitive Behavioral structure, we also look at which behaviors you might want to alter, as well as the thinking distortions that tend to be underneath our areas of dysfunction.With couples: communication, conflict management, expectations and ways to express love to each other.                                                                         
With Clinical Supervision, LCSW or LMHP: awareness of how your own patterns influence your work.With individuals, couples in therapy, or with an individual or family in a life transition, or with a professional working on his or her supervision hours, I will begin with you where you are, and with compassion and respect support you in helping you achieve your goals.

I treat those who have experienced trauma in their life, and have over 10 years of experience working with domestic violence, sexual abuse, and child abuse. I work with people of various cultures, sexual orientations, and gender identities and know that Trauma is non-discriminatory. Trauma often creates patterns and loops that extend into many areas of a person's life, and can be difficult or painful to overcome. Sometimes the way people survive their trauma brings them more pain, adds to the chaos, and reinforces negative beliefs that perpetuate the cycle.I work with clients to overcome their past, calm their bodies, and bring peace to their own lives. My practice focuses on bolstering strengths so they can face their past and find new meaning in life. I utilize a variety of techniques, such as grounding and meditation, somatic interventions, EMDR, as well as talk therapy techniques.I can hold space for you and teach you how to hold that space for yourself. Join me to learn ways to care for yourself and move past the trauma that has been haunting you. You are a survivor, and I can help you become a thriver.

Hi, I’m Janice Valdez and I am a Licensed Marriage Family therapist. My career began providing services to individuals who suffer from addiction. For the last three years I have provided individual therapy to clients of all ages with an array of different issues including depression, anxiety, grief, trauma, abuse, and more.As a therapist my approach is electic with a touch of narrative, solution focused, cognitive behavioral, DBT, and trauma focused. I provide a safe place for you to share your story. We all have as story and the good news is we are still writing it!When you are ready to tell your story I am here to listen. You have the power to make the changes to you desire, and I am her to help you through the process. I look forward to meeting you!

Are you deciding whether to fix or leave a relationship? Do you feel out of control of your feelings or frustrated that you're not enjoying life? I have 22 years of experience in helping people to develop richer connections and reduce loneliness and stress. My areas of expertise are divorce recovery, clarifying patterns to find the right partner, perinatal and postpartum changes, and step-parenting. I also have experience in working with addiction, trauma recovery, and with families affected by mental illness.Examining your expectations and relationship patterns can help you to understand what went wrong, to heal, and to redefine your future. If you are a new parent or a step-parent there are often dramatic shifts in your identity and how you see the world; therapy can be helpful.My focus is to help you gain insight, resolve conflicts, and handle stresses in your life. I am dedicated to helping you flourish in your life.

Ultimately, my job is help you get to a place where you feel satisfied with your life and no longer need therapy.

Something’s wrong, but you can’t put your finger on it. Or maybe you know what’s wrong, but don’t know what to do about it. Your child is acting out at school, at home, or with others, they are reactive or do socially inappropriate things, maybe they’re even avoidant or acting depressed. The bottom line is you’re worried, but maybe you’re also concerned that you’re overthinking it or that it’s just “how they are” and there’s nothing you can do. The truth is that these problems can be a sign of trauma, anxiety, or depression in children and they can be improved or addressed all together with the right kind of help.You can have a more satisfying relationship with your child, feel less like a failure as a parent, and look forward to school conferences. You and your child can navigate the ups and downs across developmental stages and life stressors.Dr. Ayala is one of eight people in the Sacramento area IFECMHS certified (Infant, Infant-Family, and Early Childhood Mental Health). She specializes in complex trauma/PTSD, anxiety, depression, and attachment-based issues in children and families. She is experienced working with children in the dependency, reunification  and adoption processes.

Tired of debating, searching, calling, and waiting for accessible counseling services? Change is within reach. For you, your couple, or your family member, our affordable fees make it easier than ever to get started.Michelle, Eva, Sarah, and Kristy: Our team of compassionate therapists will help you find the center of your problem and focus on it, following your progress to get you back on track. No more wondering what life could be with greater peace of mind.Anxiety, depressed mood, anger, conflict, self-esteem, brain fog: Why suffer longer? Let's get you scheduled!

Life's demands leave you feeling overwhelmed, depressed, and burned out. You don’t know who you are because you have spent your life just trying to get by. Despite having strong values, you have internalized societal standards and become your biggest critic. Sometimes you feel so different from people around you, you wonder if you will ever fit in or feel understood. Past pain and traumas continue to influence daily life, keeping you stuck in old patterns, fears, and wounds. The climate crisis and life under neoliberal capitalism leave you feeling understandably anxious and depressed.With the support of therapy, you hope to create a life that aligns with your values and needs. You want to find ways to care for and support yourself. Maybe this includes unmasking, being more present in your body, learning to accommodate your needs, finding community, or connecting to creativity.If you would like to do this work with a queer and neurodiversity-affirming therapist, I might be a good fit. To talk more about your needs and how we might work together, reach out so that we can set up a consultation. Email is preferred (If you call and get my voicemail, please leave your email address so I can respond). Thanks!

Learn how to feel more connected to yourself, others and the world around you. Therapy provides all the elements of intimacy: honest communication, vulnerability and trust. Good therapy is challenging yet warm, providing both structure and empathy for your unique experience. We are a collective of therapists with a wide range of specialties. Our intake professionals will help connect you with the right therapist for your needs. We make appointments easy, offering evenings and weekends and flexibility for creative professionals who can't make the same time each week.Therapy is a process of self-reflection and conversation that honors the struggles of life: career uncertainty, relationship decisions, loneliness, grief and the ongoing pursuit self-love. Relationship and sexual concerns, couples therapy, anxiety, addiction, trauma, eating disorders, stress management, insomnia, women's issues, creativity, LGBTQ- welcome.

Welcome! My name is Liz Trockey (she/her) and I’m a licensed marriage and family therapist who likes to use compassion, awareness building, and humor to support my clients in finding alignment within themselves. I believe that the client-therapist relationship is invaluable and recognize the privilege and honor of being able to witness emotional, relational, and spiritual growth. In the past four years, I have gained experience working with children, teens, and adults and utilize an attachment-based, trauma-informed approach to help clients find kindness and compassion for themselves.

I have spent the last 15 years working as a school psychologist, adjunct professor, and contractor. I have served students from preschool to high school aged and worked in the full range of settings from public schools, charter schools, to non-public schools. I am a proud graduate of the University of California, Davis and California State University, Sacramento. In 2010, I obtained my License as an Educational Psychologist (LEP # 3165).   I specialize in providing evidence based interventions for children with anxiety, ADHD, and autism or any combination of those issues. I also have a unique experience in that I am blessed with a child who has been diagnosed with an Autism Spectrum Disorder so I understand disability from both the parent and educator perspectives.I conduct strength based psychoeducational assessments and counseling services for individuals or groups with expertise in: ​ Anxiety/Coping Skills training through Cognitive Behavioral Interventions, Mindfulness training, Self-regulation training Social skills training. I can also help parents navigating IEP's and systems of support and/or inclusion.

Learn how to feel more connected to yourself, others and the world around you. Therapy provides all the elements of intimacy: honest communication, vulnerability and trust. Good therapy is challenging yet warm, providing both structure and empathy for your unique experience. We are a collective of therapists with a wide range of specialties. Our intake professionals will help connect you with the right therapist for your needs. We make appointments easy, offering evenings and weekends and flexibility for creative professionals who can't make the same time each week. Therapy is a process of self-reflection and conversation that honors the struggles of life: career uncertainty, relationship decisions, loneliness, grief and the ongoing pursuit self-love. Relationship and sexual concerns, couples therapy, anxiety, addiction, trauma, eating disorders, stress management, insomnia, women's issues, creativity, LGBTQ- welcome.

I strongly believe that reaching out for support is one of the bravest acts a person can do for themselves. All of us at times in our lives need someone to understand, care, and support us in taking those first steps towards healing and well-being. I use a compassionate and non-judgmental approach to therapy, while providing a warm space to support your needs and concerns. My approach is based on a collaborative process, and we will work together to create a greater awareness into who you are, while promoting positive changes that work for your individual needs. Together, we will develop tools for coping that focus on your whole health. I'm honored when clients share their journey with me, and I have a profound respect for how unique everyone's process is in finding out what is truly important to them. I have worked with individuals, couples, teens, and families. I am experienced working with anxiety, depression, PTSD, relational problems, bipolar, and grief.

Life is full of challenges. You're doing your best but may still be feeling lost and overwhelmed. As part of the LGBTQIA+ community, you want a therapist who can empathize and relate to your unique experiences. You may want to improve your relationships with others or with yourself. You may have difficulty setting boundaries and identifying your needs. Perhaps you want to heal from past traumas and develop skills to manage triggers. You might be stuck in beliefs, stories, or patterns that are no longer serving you. The good news is that obstacles can be opportunities. Let's explore them together.I am a Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist who specializes in working with the LGBTQIA+ community. My therapeutic focus encompasses trauma, attachment, relationships, self-actualization, and concrete tools for navigating life's stressors. I bring a warm, empathetic, and truthful presence as I walk alongside clients in their healing journeys.I am available for telehealth sessions in Sacramento and throughout California. I partner with an organization to accept insurance (Optum, Aetna, United Healthcare) and can provide a superbill for private pay. Reach out for a free consultation where we can explore whether we'd be a good fit.

Are you feeling held back by anxiety and your inner self-critic? Does this keep you from creating the change you want for yourself? Or maybe you are juggling so many responsibilities that your own needs come last? Is it hard to take time for yourself? If you answered yes to any of these questions, please know that you aren’t alone and therapy can help. I work with adult clients struggling with anxiety and relationship challenges, and I am particularly passionate about supporting moms through pregnancy and beyond. I offer Telehealth therapy to clients throughout CA, and in person therapy to clients in the Sacramento Area.My approach to therapy is highly strength-based and collaborative. We will work together to identify your goals and how best to get you there. Based on each client's unique needs, I draw on strategies from various therapeutic modalities, such as Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, Mindfulness, and Emotion Focused Therapy.I firmly believe that we all have inherent strengths, resources, and the capacity for change. These values guide everything I do as a therapist.  I am here to help you build on your strengths and create the change you want for yourself. Please reach out for a free 15 minute phone consultation to see if working together feels like a fit for you.

I work with adults and couples using a relational approach that emphasizes connection: being seen, heard, and valued for who you are and where you are in your journey. My goal is to create a welcoming, nurturing, non-judgmental space where you feel safe to share your needs and explore the factors and patterns that may be impacting your quality of life. As an immigrant, I am particularly sensitive to the many ways different people show vulnerability, and strive to take multicultural, interpersonal, and contextual factors into account in order to get to know the multiple identities forming our whole selves.I have a direct and transparent approach, and work collaboratively to identify goals and tailor treatment to your specific needs. I practice research supported therapies and often draw from humanistic, cognitive behavioral and mindfulness based techniques. I have received specialized training in EFT for couples, CBT, DBT & Motivational Interviewing.I believe everyone is capable and worthy of healthy relationships with themselves and others. I feel so grateful for the opportunity to help clients increase awareness of and comfort with emotions, improve relationships, and achieve a more balanced and fulfilling life. Please contact me for a consultation to find out if I may be a good fit for you.

As a queer relationship and sex therapist, I am passionate about supporting folks create the relationships and sex lives they want!  Do you feel overwhelmed, anxious, frustrated and alone in this world as you do your best to connect to others?  Maybe social anxiety is holding you back.  Maybe you aren’t quite where you want to be in your relationships or career.  Maybe adulting is … well… kinda crappy? I use humor, down to earth therapeutic conversations, and evidence-based skills.  Visit lovehealgrow.com to learn more or scheduling online today.  In person appointments available!I’m the type of therapist who knows sometimes life doesn’t lead where you expect it to.  And that can be scary, disappointing, ironic…or even wonderful.  Life has ups and downs.  When you’re reaching out for therapy you might feel like you’re on a downward spiral.  But I will make space to see you for your strengths, hopes, and dreams, too.I am all for challenging the traditional or what society tells us is the way things "should" be.  Your relationships, your career, your sexual desires-if you are trying to fit in the box that society says is "normal" you might find that you're feeling stressed, anxious, and depressed.  Let's work through this together in therapy!

Are you feeling anxious, overwhelmed, or struggling with life stressors? I provide solution-focused therapy utilizing a variety of modalities including CBT, DBT, and EMDR. My approach is positive, optimistic, and accepting. Let me help you walk through life's challenges to become the best version of yourself!

Whether you’re struggling with a crisis, life transition, feeling overwhelmed, or finding yourself stuck in unproductive patterns, there is no need to navigate this on your own. Therapy is about exploring the self in a way that allows you to grow through self-discovery. I focus on meeting clients where they are and seeing the world from their perspective, and go together from there.As a psychotherapist, I’ve worked with various populations and people facing different challenges, including depression, anxiety, trauma, substance use, suicidal ideation and self-harm.I am passionate about working with individuals from all cultures, while providing a safe, non-judgmental and collaborative therapeutic process so we can work together toward your desired goals. I look forward to supporting you achieve self-acceptance and compassion, healing and growth.

For many people, standard 12 step-dominated substance use treatment does not work.  People may tell you that your problem is a lack of willingness, or that you are in "denial."  But maybe you need someone to listen to you rather than talk at you.  The fact that these programs do not work for you does not mean that you are not capable of change.  It probably just means that you have not found an approach that addresses your individual needs and values.Harm reduction is a philosophy which meets you where you are rather than imposing rigid demands.  My name is Jeremy Prillwitz, and I’m a Licensed Advanced Alcohol and Drug Counselor (LAADC).   I have worked as a harm reduction-based counselor for the past ten years.    My expertise is evidence-based treatment, but YOU are the expert on your life.Let's work together to learn the underlying causes of your struggles with substances, and to find solutions which address those causes.  Merely treating symptoms or following someone else's recipe for recovery is unlikely to bring lasting change.  If you are empowered to seek out your own truth, you will find the right answers.  I can help you do that.

An ideal client would be someone who is empathetic toward others and compassionate toward themselves and is open, coachable, and capable of accepting feedback. The process of therapy takes time and energy so having someone start the process of therapy with an open mind and a willingness to put in the work to see the process through is also helpful.  Jennifer also offers clinical supervision to pre-licensed therapists (ASW, AMFT, APCC). In addition to therapy and supervision, she provides consulting to therapists seeking to start or grow their private practice. She's also passionate in counseling other mental health providers.She specializes in helping individuals reach their goals whether it be optimizing a relationship, a career change, managing grief, or just feeling overall better. Jennifer also works with couples and families, and she is happy to adjust her therapeutic approach to match the needs of her clients and meet them wherever they are at. As therapy is a very personal and impactful process, I would be happy to do a phone consultation to discuss the your specific needs and if the services that could be provided as a result of my life and work experience, education, and personality would be a good fit.

paragraph_descriptions: We often come to points in life that leave us feeling lost, stuck and untethered. Whether you are grappling with anxiety, depression, addiction, trauma, relationship issues, or beyond, you are not alone. I am a Licensed Clinical Social Worker and would be honored to work with you. For many, therapy can provide a safe space to unpack and explore your feelings, experiences, thoughts, and fears while aligning with your values, goals and hopes to become more present, connected and fulfilled in your life. The relationship is key to this process and I strive to understand you, your identity, and your background.I utilize evidence based practices including but not limited to Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT), Trauma Informed Care, and Harm Reduction. I work to ensure that individuals feel supported and empowered while holding safe space for self-reflection, guidance, connection, validation, self-awareness, and self-determination.Prioritizing your wellbeing by coming to therapy is a brave, challenging, and monumental step! Welcome. I take a non-judgmental stance intent on reducing shame, aligning with values and increasing self-worth and self-compassion. My goal is to partner and collaborate with you and to provide support, safety, feedback, and compassion on this courageous journey.

Are you struggling with behaviors that cause disruption and chaos within your home?  Do you feel exhausted and frustrated that you lack the positive interactions with your child that you deeply desire? I can help guide you through the noise and chaos so that you can build a strong and nurturing relationship with your child and enhance your family dynamic. I have a talent for understanding people and their individual needs and qualities. I see what drives them and what holds them back.  Behaviors that may seem negative to others, make sense to me as I’m able to see their function.Once you and your family feel understood, I can offer strategies and skills to reduce behaviors causing distress in the family, increase positive interactions, and ultimately help build a more cohesive and harmonious family unit. I will work with your family in your home, community, or the traditional office setting depending on the needs of your family.With over 20 years of experience working with children, adolescents, and families, I have successfully provided intervention for a diverse array of families and children with disruptive behaviors. I welcome challenges, I’m creative, and I see things others miss.

Welcome, I appreciate your interest in exploring the options of my practice. As a registered Art Therapist and Marriage and Family Therapist my approach tends to be interactive. I value a strength-based perspective with clients that focuses on identifying and building strengths as a means to achieve your goals, especially approaches to well being and happiness. I often use solution-focused and narrative approaches that include skill building through cognitive-behavioral techniques. I provide a variety of modalities to address clients' needs which includes art therapy groups for teens and adults as means of support and expression.My training specializations have included trauma-focused CBT, as well as neurologically informed trauma therapy using art with children and adolescents, grief/bereavement work with all populations. I have also worked in residential dual diagnosis settings with adolescents, and more recently with children and families in foster settings, and military familiesPlease feel free to contact me either through leaving voice mail or an email with best time to contact you for brief consultation.

Hello, welcome to my practice. I offer mental health services in California and Washington via telehealth. I have been working with youth, adults, and families since 2010. Are you going through a difficult time in your life? Have you had experiences that are impacting your ability to thrive? Are you struggling with anxiety and depression? Is your child struggling in school or at home? I want to help you identify your strengths and weaknesses and identify more healthy coping skills and communication techniques. I am committed to supporting you and your family in your journey toward well-being and recovery.My hope is that I can be someone that can walk alongside you on your journey and provide the extra support you need to meet your goals. I use a range of therapeutic techniques, and I believe in working collaboratively with my clients. Lifespan Integration is an additional therapeutic tool that I can offer.Feel free to reach out to me via phone or email anytime. I am happy to schedule a phone consultation to discuss your needs and determine if we would be a good fit for each other. My goal is to always help clients find a therapist that is the best fit for them, whether it is with me or with someone else.

Each struggle you face is worthy of exploration and deserving of healing! Relationships with ourselves, our families, friends, and partners can change over time. I help couples and individuals create the life and relationships they want--I have a special interest in supporting young adults as they navigate relationships, adulting, perfectionism, and stress-related to figuring it all out.  Visit www.lovehealgrow.com to learn more.I believe in creating a helpful space for couples and individuals to safely explore and heal from difficult emotions, thoughts, and patterns.  I am committed to truly understanding you and where you’d like to go next. Together, we will work to help you gain new insights, heal wounds both old and new, and experience growth and empowerment.First and foremost, my work is client-centered. I strive to build meaningful relationships with my clients to help foster resilience and confidence. I recognize the courage it takes to engage in therapy and believe that no matter what brings you, you are deserving of love and acceptance.  Schedule with me online at www.lovehealgrow.com.

Have you or a loved one struggled with alcohol or drug dependency? Allow me to help you on your journey to recovery. At Life Steps Consulting, we know that life is full of different transitions, which can be broken down into a series of steps. When you are struggling with substance abuse, movement through the transitional steps halts, causing you to fall into unhealthy life cycles, which impact your career goals, relationships, physical and mental health. I can help you get back on track. I not only have studied the disease of alcohol and drug addiction, but I have been there and I know how you feel.My name is William Schneider and I’m a Licensed Advanced Alcohol Drug Counselor. I have worked in the recovery field for over 15 years and my focus is providing you with comprehensive addiction counseling. I offer individual sessions, couples counseling, family counseling, substance abuse evaluations for family and legal courts,  and intervention services.I know from personal experience addiction doesn't just affect one area in a person's life, but that it affects multiple areas. I offer a client-centered approach where we explore those areas and provide you support with tapping into your inner strengths and applying them to your recovery goals.

I have been licensed as a Marriage, Family Therapist for over 20 years. As a trained and experienced therapist, my education background includes MS in Counseling Marriage, Family, and Child Counseling, MS in Psychology, and Doctor of Psychology from the University of La Verne, California.  My passion is to help my clients develop meaningful behavioral changes and learn coping strategies to use to navigate through life struggles. It takes courage to ask for help and I take it seriously to create an emotionally safe environment where my clients can speak freely about their struggles with no judgment.During my time as a therapist, I have been exposed to a range of clientele and have realized my areas of interest and expertise. I work with clients with depression, anxiety, fear, postpartum depression, relationship and couple issues, and grief.  I am trained in a range of modalities and recognize that not all clients need the same approach.I am trained in Solution Focused, CBT, Motivational Interviewing, Family Systems, and Feedback Informed Care.  I look forward to working with you and breaking down the barriers that hinder your growth. Let me help you write a new story for your life.

Frustrated? Unhappy? Want some insight and change? I offer an encouraging approach to help you explore your world in a therapeutic environment. I believe that everyone is the expert of their own experience; you have lived your life longer than I have known you. I often use the metaphor of being a flashlight in a dark cave, shedding light on different things, however, you, as the client are in the driver's seat; I am in the passenger seat, as a co-driver. Together, we will explore your personal meanings and experiences while making larger connections to your goals.  I invite you to our journey together in creating new meaning.I offer psychotherapy & a relational view regarding anxiety, grief/loss, body image/self esteem/ weight issues, intimacy problems, divorce, pre-marital, LGBT issues, and military related issues. I also have experience working with couple related issues as well. Please also check out my website for further information ("services" tab). I also have a specialization with cultural and racial issues, and have an interest in working with interracial and intercultural couples and families. I also have experience working with clients regarding parenting/co-parenting, sibling/coworker/relationships. In addition, addiction/substance, trauma, and domestic violence.

We are all a work-in-progress, capable of change at any age. Are you hitting a wall with stress? Curious about making a career shift? Struggling with grief? Longing to strengthen your relationship? Wishing you could be more confident? Trying to adjust to changes? Feeling burnt out from caregiving pressures? Longing for some insight? Needing tools to help with anxiety and depression? Wanting accountability with goals and healthy habits? Each new day offers another opportunity to learn, grow, and become who we want to be. You don't have to do it alone. Therapy can help with this process.I bring warmth, positivity, humor, and zero judgment to my work with individuals, couples, and families. I help people navigate the ups and downs of family life, big transitions, relationships, and other challenges. I believe in the healing power of creativity, and I encourage those who might benefit to play with the possibilities.  Therapy is special because it is time in your week just for you to get to know yourself better, build on your strengths, and work with a skilled and compassionate teammate who can help you bloom where you are planted.

Life is hard.  In one moment, life as you know it can be completely changed. Are the things that once made you happy no longer making you happy? Have you been through a frightening experience that left you feeling scared, lonely, or even doubting who you are? Maybe you’ve been through a series of little things that you believe shouldn’t be bothering you, but they are. Do you feel completely misunderstood and alone? I get it. You are not alone.  Everyone needs space to process life’s challenges and successes. No one is supposed to be able to figure it all out on their own.In our work together, you'll build the coping skills you need, discover what holds you back and ultimately what empowers you. In every session, you'll learn tools to help you heal. We will work together to help you feel more calm, confident and happy through research proven techniques like CBT, DBT and Solutions Focus focused therapy.Together, we will start creating the life you’ve always wanted. You want to relax with your friends, family, and your pets. You want to be able to turn your brain off and enjoy a good book. You want to love yourself, like you love others. You are ready to feel the confidence and ease that everyone else seems to see. Through therapy, this is achievable.

Are you experiencing big changes in life?  Such as transitioning into retirement, adjusting to a health-related changes, chronic illness, changes related to your work, or uncertainty around what path you you want to choose for yourself and your future?  I'm here to help.  I work one on one (individual therapy) with adults of all ages utilizing an integrative, relational, strength-based approach - while tailoring treatment to each persons specific needs & goals.   LGBTQ+ affirmative & allied.I have enjoyed working with a diverse population of individuals in many different settings across the continuum of care.  I am a Clinical Psychologist with additional training in health psychology and a background of working within multidisciplinary treatment teams.  I offer therapy primarily via video appointments (available to any resident of CA).Please send me a message (I'm able to respond the quickest this way) and we can start down the path of improving your quality of life and creating the changes that you want.  If you're looking for additional information about me or my approach, please go to www.drcarrierogers.com

I am a Licensed Marriage and Family therapist specializing in self actualization. I want you to recognize you have the tools and strength to develop and manage all your challenges.  I am just a guide to help illuminate your journey.  It is your life.  Live well. After many twists and turns, I now have over a decade of experience healing the effects of addiction and comorbid mental health disorders as a Therapist and Clinical Director. I am always filled with gratitude for witnessing the courage people find to grow into their best selves and am prepared to assist when you are ready to start.

Is the stress of your life overwhelming you? Or has a past experience left you stuck and unable to move forward? You're likely fed up with how anxiety or trauma have crippled your ability to function in everyday life, isolating you from others, and leaving you feeling trapped or hopeless. You might not even remember a time you didn’t feel this way. But one thing is for sure: you’re ready for some relief. You’re ready to feel confident again. You’re ready to experience a sense of ease. Most of all, you’re ready to reclaim a sense of control over your life.Clients come to me looking for a therapist who "gets" what happened to them on a deeper level, because therapy should be a place where you feel safe and understood. Sessions with me are focused on giving you the resources you need to be successful in taking control of your life again, always at a pace you feel in control of and comfortable with.As an experienced therapist who specializes in anxiety, PTSD/trauma, ADHD, and Autism, I believe that everyone can heal and reclaim control over their lives. You don’t have to continue feeling overwhelmed or trapped, and you don’t have to do it alone. Call or message me today for a free consultation.

Thinking of seeking therapy with a professional that can assist in providing suggestions on how to improve your daily living, decision making, relationships, and career choices? Do you want help with learning coping skills that can aid you during stressful times, your anxiety, depression, and/or trauma? Or, just want someone to talk to that can remain neutral when sharing complex issues or mental health struggles?I can provide support and guidance, including working together in order for you to overcome the present struggles you are experiencing. My goal is to guide you as you rediscover who you are beyond the affects of trauma and mental health illness, find your self-worth and boost your self-esteem, and hold that space where you find your happiness.I have experience and specialize working with children, adolescents, young adults, and families dealing with dilemmas of abuse/neglect, grief and loss, depression, anxiety, trauma, intimate partner violence, substance use, abandonment, and life transitions. My approach is having transparency, be exploratory, humanistic, & trauma-informed.

Your past does not define who you are today and who you want to be. Life can be challenging and sometimes adverse experiences can affect how we view and navigate the world. These experiences often leave us feeling powerless, hopeless, disconnected, and alone. Our responses to stress and trauma are individual and personal. We feel like we’re treading water without the right guidance.  This is exhausting and interferes with our well-being. We just want to be seen and heard and know how to move past it all.I am a relational and trauma therapist. With years of experience working in diverse clinical settings with clients struggling with varied life challenges, there’s not much I haven’t seen.  I provide therapy using evidence-based tools. My clients walk away from therapy with me feeling validated, supported, and confident in using the skills they've learned.My lived experiences make me a better therapist. When we work together, you won't just get a trained therapist. You'll get someone who truly understands what you're going through.

I work with LGBTQIA+ adults, couples, and teens. Together we will navigate relationship issues, sexuality, trauma, anxiety-and whatever is keeping you stuck right now.  Life is really hard sometimes and when we are attacked for our identity on a global level, we go through everything that life throws at us with additional fear and minority stress.  You are not alone, let's work together towards a joyful and fulfilling life and relationships. Visit lovehealgrow.com to schedule or learn more.I’m the kind of therapist who welcomes every part of you. From things that may feel unmentionable or overwhelming, to your greatest joys, hopes, and moments of peace. I’m attentive, warm, creative, and genuine. I will take time to listen, wonder, and learn with you, while also bringing practical, evidenced based tools and insight.Together we’ll make space for the breadth of emotions and experiences you’ve had. We can have fun in therapy, grieve, grow, celebrate, change, process, and fortify the countless strengths and tools you already have. I look forward to getting to know you and your goals and working alongside you!  Schedule online at www.lovehealgrow.com today!

As a therapist, my focus is on helping you cultivate greater self-love, self-care, and personal growth. I created “Behold your Wonder” for all identifying as women. I want to empower you to recognize and appreciate your unique qualities and strengths, so you can feel more confident, resilient, and better equipped to navigate life's challenges. My goal is to support you by providing guidance and education so that you can have self-agency and build secure attachments. Furthermore, I also provide couples therapy to help couples cultivate greater intimacy, connection, and healthier communication.My therapeutic approach is integrative and provides empathy and warmth. I help individuals and couples to develop better relationships with themself and others. I am a Certified Clinical Trauma Professional (CCTP), and I am also working towards certification as an Emotionally Focused Therapist.It takes a lot of courage to seek therapy and take steps toward personal growth, and I am honored to begin the conversation with you.

Although I have a short waitlist at this time, please feel free to reach out as openings can happen at any time. My services are 100% virtual at this time and I can assure you I feel just as connected to my tele-health clients as with in-person sessions. Through a Psychodynamic approach that incorporates Cognitive Behavioral techniques, a Solution-Focused approach & Life Coaching skills, I offer support and guidance as you deal with stressors, changes or challenges that have arisen, as well as on-going issues you may be experiencing. I have worked successfully with clients of all ethnicities & socio-economic levels.My goal is to provide the validation, support and guidance you need as well as help you gain insight, awareness and any necessary skills specific to your journey. My strength is helping individuals learn skills and strategies to cope with the varied life stressors, changes, blindsides, challenges, losses and curveballs that come our way.My goal and commitment is to help you through life's trials and tribulations and to help you find learning, growth, positive change, understanding/acceptance and healing. I look forward to connecting with you. Send an email or call so we can schedule a 15 min consult and please make sure to mention what if any insurance you are using.

Thank you for visiting my profile. My practice specializes in sensitively helping you identify the challenges that are keeping you from being the very best version of yourself. I work from a variety of evidence-based therapy practices to help you achieve your fullest potential. I provide a safe and protected place to talk about your life goals, your values, your wishes and your heart-felt concerns. I have over 22 years of clinical experience and am well-versed in a variety of therapy approaches that I can tailor to your own unique life circumstances. Allow me to assist you.I am a sensitive & intuitive male therapist that was raised in a spiritual home by a single parent. I honor the thoughts & feelings of anyone coming to me for guidance. I value the trust people place in me to help them and support them. I rely on faith, my intuition and 20 + years of clinical experience to guide our transformative work.I personally know how terrible anxiety feels when it takes over our life. I know what depression does to our minds and the unhelpful thoughts that it can plant inside of us. I will do my best to try and understand and to validate your personal situation. I am here to help, and will strive to provide you with a caring, respectful and professional experience.

Esta sufriendo un dolor emocional o espiritual? El dolor es señal que estamos listos para un cambio en nuestras vidas. Yo lo puedo guíar a empezar a hacer cambios importantes en su vida personal. Al ponerse en contacto conmigo quiero que reconosca que usted estara haciendo mucho del trabajo pero yo estare aqui con usted para orientarlo y apoyarle. Yo le recordare cuales son sus fuerzas y lo retaré a que encuentre adentro de usted las ganas de mejorar su situación. Yo crecí en un hogar de fé y esperanza. Mí mama fue mama solterá y yo vi el gran esfuerzo que ella hiso para sacar a su familia adelante sola. Yo entiendo que hablar con un profesional es dificil. Espero que al conocerme se sienta como que habla con un amigo que esta aquí para entenderle y apoyarle. Le puedo ayudar! No tiene que sufrir solo o solá. Llameme.A todos nos sirve hablar con alguien de ves en cuando. Permitame poner mis casi 20 años de experencia a sus ordenes. Yo sé lo que se siente tener ansiedad y depresion. De todo corazón trataré de entender su situación única y ofrecerle todo mi apoyo posible. Si usted esta listo para realizar esta nueva etapa de su vida, no demorre mas. Llamemé hoy!

Please note-my practice is full. I do have one in person spot, every other week, on Thursdays at 3 opening up soon. Contact me if interested.Why live with the symptoms of anxiety, depression, guilt, or shame, when therapy can offer relief? It is possible to learn new coping skills at any age! I also offer specialized services for the LGBT community, including trans children, teens and adults,  as well as for those living with the often overwhelming symptoms of tinnitus.I love being a therapist and believe in the ability of all people to change, no matter what life stage you are in. There are always reasons to be hopeful in what life can bring, and what we can create. I am very flexible in my approach, and offer weekly or bi-weekly appointments, when I have availability.  Together, we can make change happen! You deserve it.

paragraph_descriptions: As James Baldwin famously said, "not everything that is faced can be changed, but nothing can be changed unless faced", I also offer you the following poem: "When we feel safe, anything is possible. We become unstoppable. Because we have a firm ground to launch and a safe ground to land. We can then stand. Voice ourselves, show ourselves. Life becomes a dance."I look forward to learning about the journey that brought you to explore personal growth and self-discovery. Please feel free to visit www.dramirramezani.com/health for more information about individual, family, classes/educational, and assessment services.I also offer the following ongoing, televideo classes: Foundations of Mindfulness and Compassion Class • Online Mindful Self-Compassion (MSC) • Mindfulness-Based Cognitive Therapy (MBCT) • Mindfulness-Based Stress Reduction (MBSR). To learn more, signed up, or be placed on waitlist, please visit www.dramirramezani.com/education for details.

I enjoy supporting individuals, couples, and families from all age groups and all ethnic backgrounds. I firmly believe that we all possess unique strengths and expertise that we might tap into to support our healing and growth, therefore, focusing our therapeutic relationship approach on strength-based by supporting you to develop the desire you seek. I provide an unbiased, non-judgmental, and safe environment to explore our perceived challenges. I strive to empower your mental and holistic health to uncover the light that shines within you.The theoretical orientations that I utilize to support your growth include Multigenerational Family Therapy,  Narrative Therapy,  Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, and Dialectical Behavioral Therapy while integrating Mindfulness skills and Gratefulness practice.“Owning our story can be hard but not nearly as difficult as spending our lives running from it. Embracing our vulnerabilities is risky but not nearly as dangerous as giving up on love, belonging, and joy" – Brené Brown

When our lives are destabilized it's hard to think and emotions are rocking.  At the very same time that more is asked of us, new stressors may amplify old self-doubt.  A therapist can ask questions that lead to new behaviors - helping you find your wise mind and accepting what you must - so you may reclaim strength. There are tools that can support your path towards resilience.  If symptoms have made their way into your daily functioning, don't stay in a place of misery.  Let me help you get back to your best self.I believe healing is an emotion/mind/body experience. I am a DBT therapist who loves to bring mindfulness into learning new behaviors. I will support the focus on your desired outcome for therapy, while bringing my experience to the table to assist. If you do the work I trust you'll find ways to suffer less and to make your life worth living.When I moved to California I experienced a significant JOLT!  Nearly everything changed and I lost most of my support system and some of my self.  Following wise guidance I invested in the people and activities that brought joy.  Most importantly, I learned to talk less and to DO more!  What is your story?  What do you fear? What strengths can you count on?

I am a clinical psychologist whose interests and experience include trauma, mental health, physical health, chronic pain, happiness, well-being, immigration, and diversity issues.  I believe we all have the capacity within us to improve our lives, in one way or another, but sometimes we need some guidance. In my work, I try to teach my patients what is happening with their minds and bodies, as well as skills they can utilize to get better. Education is very important, and it makes a difference in the way we make changes.    I provide services that are welcoming, compassionate, genuine, and have your best interest at heart. For issues affecting mental and/or physical health, trauma, relationships, chronic pain, happiness, wellbeing, immigration and diversity issues, it is always a pleasure for me to witness your personal growth and increased functionality. I can work with people using various therapies, hypnosis, psychological assessments, and forensic immigration evaluations. We all come across difficulties in our lives at some point, some big some small. If something is keeping you from living life to the fullest and achieving your full potential, don’t hesitate to reach out for help. The life you love could be within your reach in less time than you imagine!

Soy una psicóloga clínica cuyos intereses y experiencias incluyen trauma, salud mental, salud física, dolor crónico, felicidad, bienestar, inmigración, y diversidad. Yo soy de la creencia que todos tenemos la capacidad de mejorar nuestras vidas, de una manera u otra, pero algunas veces necesitamos alguna guía. En my trabajo con usted, Yo trato de enseñar que está pasando con el cuerpo y la mente, al igual que proveer herramientas que pueda utilizar para mejorar. La educación es muy importante, y hace una gran diferencia en la manera en que hacemos cambios. Yo proveo servicios que son afectuosos, compasivos, y genuinos.Para casos que afectan su salud mental y/o física, trauma, relaciones, dolor crónico, felicidad, bienestar, inmigración y razones de diversidad, es un placer para mi ver cómo su vida personal y funcionamiento mejora. Yo trabajo usando varios tipos de terapias, hipnosis, exámenes psicológicos, y evaluaciones psicológicas forenses para casos de inmigración.Todos nos topamos con dificultades, grandes o pequeñas, en algún punto en la vida. Si hay algo que le está previniendo vivir su vida al máximo y lograr su potencial, no dude en pedir ayuda. La vida que usted desea puede estar a su alcance en menos tiempo de lo que se imagina!

Do you struggle on the inside, even if others see you as capable? Maybe you criticize yourself or think you should be achieving more. I work with people who are successful in some areas and not in others. They may be frequently frustrated, disappointed, ashamed, or even angry, but they don’t know why. So they beat themselves up, hide their pain, and often give up on their dreams. As a therapist, I help my adult and adolescent clients discover how to respect, trust, and care for themselves, so they can live life fully again.To tailor treatment, I will listen with care and respect for where you want to be and where you have been. I often work with individuals who deal with loss, chronic medical conditions, marginalized identity, situational or multi-generational trauma, and so balance a developmental lens, a sociocultural perspective and strengths-based approaches.Therapy is often a dance between challenge and encouragement. Once we've established trust in the relationship, I help my clients safely face whatever is happening or has happened to them; I specialize in noticing and drawing your attention to moments of success. I welcome a conversation to see if my approach is the right fit for you and your concerns.

Are you feeling anxious, overwhelmed, or stuck? Perhaps struggling with certain relationships in your life? If so, I can help. Through therapy we can explore the patterns, thoughts, beliefs and behaviors that shape your world and help you identify and challenge areas that are holding you back.While I treat a variety of personal and interpersonal issues, I have a special interest in helping undergraduate and graduate level students cope with anxiety, self-esteem challenges, and relationship issues. I use an integrative model, collaborating with you to develop individualized treatment plans to address your specific goals.I am also a certified yoga instructor and enjoy incorporating mindfulness, and yoga into the therapeutic relationship when appropriate. Call or e-mail me today with any questions. I am happy to talk to you to figure out what counseling option is best for you.     I am currently  accepting new Telehealth clients available for video sessions when appropriate.

Life often takes us to a place where thriving feels like an impossible task, then leaves us feeling like we've lost ourselves. If you feel like you're stuck in a cycle that doesn't bring you peace or if you feel like you've almost forgotten how safety feels, I am here to offer support.	 			 			 			 			 			 I primarily work with individuals who struggle with anxiety, trauma-related disorders, eating disorders, and BPD. I have been fortunate to have worked with and am passionate in working with the Asian, Asian-American (and other POC), and LGBTQ+ communities.I utilize Attachment-Focused EMDR and talk therapy, Emotion-Focused Individual Therapy (EFIT), and interventions from Narrative Therapy and Dialectical Behavior Therapy.When you feel ready to create the changes you want to see and feel, reach out for a free phone consultation. I am here to provide a safe space and assist you in your process.

Are you feeling overwhelmed or “stuck”? Are you wanting more from life? Are you struggling with letting go, changing, getting rid of and/or avoiding difficult and painful thoughts and feelings? Utilizing a genuinely warm, humorous, and direct humanistic approach, I will gently challenge you and invite you to step out of your current comfort zone and step into authentic, mindful living. Throughout our sessions, we will: hold space for difficult thoughts and feelings, highlight underlying patterns of thinking and behaving that may no longer serve you, and imagine new ways of being and doing.I utilize experiential and value-driven behavioral techniques to encourage clients to practice and integrate the skills cultivated during our sessions together into their daily lives. As an Indigenous (Northern Sierra Miwok) woman and scholar, I greatly appreciate the complex individual and collective contexts and narratives that each of us embody and enact.I believe it essential to explore and appreciate where we have come from in order to understand who we are and who we will become. Overall, I am committed to fostering an open and safe environment to support you and honor your experiences as you continue upon your lifelong journey of self-love and growth. I look forward to working with you soon.

"The curious paradox is that when I accept myself as I am then I can change."  - Dr. Carl Rogers.  We emphasize to every person who comes through our door that they are the experts in their care.  We provide the space and proper conditions to help this person live their life to their fullest potential.Hello.  We are Humanistic Center for Clinical Counseling, a group practice that places emphasis in Person-Centered/Humanistic Psychology.  We believe that everyone who comes into our office that has seen personal successes come to fruition have done so on their own accord.  We just provide the relationship to allow that potential to actualize.We understand how challenging it can be reaching out for help especially if you are unfamiliar with the counseling process.  We invite you to give us a call or email us anytime so we can go over any concerns or questions you might have.  We look forward to getting to know you.

I specialize in helping couples and individuals (especially men) heal from bad relationship experiences and build better ones with those around them, whether those relationships are with peers, family or romantic partners. I have a great breadth of experience working with children, teens and young adults in various capacities, and thus have something special to offer struggling parents, and young adults going through major life transitions.I can help persons 16+ with individual therapy, and couples 18+ with relationship issues. I take a special interest in pre-marital counseling for people of all beliefs and backgrounds who wish to protect and grow their love across a lifetime. I'm a very friendly person and have a knack for exploring the deep roots underlying your struggles and hopes alike.Using deep intellectual and emotional analysis, I create atmospheres of curiosity, creativity and good-humor to build skills and the self-awareness needed to truly grow. I also care deeply for the people I work with. So reach out to me trusting that whatever you struggle with, whatever you have done - I promise to see and find the best in you.

My work lies in helping those whose relationships and overall life connections are being negatively impacted by symptoms of depression, anxiety, or trauma. Each has its own way of showing up uninvited.  Lack of confidence and or clarity tends to blur one's path in moving forward and making decisions. Whether it's a life transition in loss, relationships, feeling stuck, or that "I just don't know", my goal is to help you create a personalized space for growth, discovery, and healing that you will carry with confidence into your life journey.I honor the humanness that is far too often forgotten or maybe intentionally "set aside".  My approach is integrated, which allows me to remain open and attuned to my clients. I use elements from CBT, person-centered, emotion-focused & strength-based therapies. I strive to maintain focus on mind, body, and emotion, to integrate the entire human experience.Whatever your situation, you've come this far.  Call me or email me so we can connect and make sure you are comfortable enough to move forward at your own pace.

During our lives we all need a place where we feel safe, comfortable, and supported to help us give direction to the lives we aspire to. Sometimes that is realizing that we need to seek help from a third-party, non-judgmental professional to help build the tools and confidence to get there. If you need help making changes in your life, big or small, this can be a great place to start. We will work on what you want to feel more of and what you want to feel less of.I am non-judgmental, straight-forward, warm and supportive therapist. I utilize empathy, compassion, and humor to help my clients feel comfortable and heard. Every individual is different. I adjust therapy modalities as appropriate to create individualized treatment plans. Every individual and couple is unique and I treat them as so.It can be difficult to reach out and ask for help and beginning therapy can be intimidating at times. Know that we will start where you are now and work to get to where you want to be. Contact me for a free 15 minute consultation to see if we will be the right fit. It is important that you find the right therapist for you.

Life circumstances change and managing life stage transitions is challenging. You might feel helpless, hopeless, and alone in trying to cope with relationship issues and troublesome or debilitating symptoms of depression, anxiety, and trauma. As a therapist with a warm, relational style and a commitment to compassionate, evidence-based interventions, my goal is to help you discover your true potential. I use a holistic approach which may include a combination of Cognitive-Behavioral and Insight-based therapies, mindfulness strategies, emotion regulation, and communication skills training.I'll provide a safe, non-judgmental, and honest atmosphere for expressing your concerns and working towards your goals. I have extensive experience in supporting children, adults, and families that find themselves in crisis, transition and major life change. I'll honor your lived experiences, values, and cultures while exploring your strengths and struggles.Together we will help you create a life that is in alignment with what's most important to you whether you'd like to improve the quality of your relationships, health, work/schooling, address mental health challenges, such as anxiety, depression, loss, and trauma.  I invite you to reach out to learn about my approach and what you can expect working with me.

Hi! I'm Rebeks (they/them) - a transmasculine nonbinary therapist who specializes in trauma, LGBTQIA+ affirmative therapy, and life with chronic illness, disability, college/academia, and affirmative approaches to neurodiversity such as Autism, ADHD, and OCD. I love working with folx in the "gray spaces" of identity who aren't quite sure they are (fill in the blank)  enough. My approach to therapy is to provide solidity and a sense of containment to enable the deeper healing-work — especially for those with complex trauma, dissociation and early attachment ruptures.I'm not here to help you adjust better to the unjust, but rather to reject the oppressive messages we all have internalized and reclaim your authentic self. I utilize a range of modalities, including attachment-based reparative approaches & EMDR, to help you create a fulfilling life that is more than the sum of what happened to you.I fundamentally believe that you can heal - actually heal - no matter how impossible that sounds or what you have lived through. I will hold that hope until you believe it too. Reach out and let's see if I'm a good therapeutic fit for you!

Self-reflection is so beneficial in therapy. I have 12 years of experience counseling adults and teens by helping them apply practical coping skills to manage their moods.  My clients often deal with feelings of overwhelm, anxiety, depression, relationship conflict, being overly sensitive, low self-esteem, multiple stressors, burnout, & ADHD. They want to increase task completion and move toward their full potential. I can help you update your mindset to be less critical of yourself, help you maintain a healthy schedule, process stressors & trauma, and grow self-confidence.  Sessions are for you & your care!We can set weekly goals for you, and I offer guidance and assist you with accountability to reach your goals. We work collaboratively to help you erode patterns that no longer serve you. My therapeutic approach is Eclectic. I combine Compassion Focused Therapy, Acceptance & Commitment Therapy, Psychodynamic, Solution Focused, Inner Child Therapy, and CBT.I'm passionate about helping others and have been very successful at counseling children, teens and adults.  I enjoy assisting people in reducing their critical voice within & updating their mindset to access their compassionate brains. We can customize tangible coping skills to mitigate stressors and move you towards living a more valued life!

I am a Person Centered, Experiential, Solution  Focused Therapist. I work with children, teens and adults in individual, couple and family formats.  I want to help you reach your goals and increase positive functioning.  II have offices in Vacaville and Yuba City California. I offer support and insight through objectivity and the opportunity  to process, negotiate and navigate situations in life.  I can attend IEP's and court proceedings at an hourly costs that include prep and travel time.There is no judgement here... this is a safe place.  You are the expert in your life and I want to help you reach your goals.

I believe that change is always possible and it's never too late to start the process. The pandemic has impacted us all in different ways and you are not alone. I work in a collaborative, eclectic, with my clients.  I provide a safe space for you to learn and practice new skills- free of judgment. If you are ready to improve your life and open to discovering new options to life's challenges, I can help. Invest in yourself and creating the life you deserve.I am trained to teach DBT skills and CBT techniques. I have worked extensively with individuals in recovery/addiction issues-am 12 Step friendly. I am a Licensed Professional Clinical Counselor with a scope that includes families, children, and couples. I am a Board-Certified Art Therapist and love to utilize this creative modality if clients are open to it!I have 25+ years professional experience working in the mental health field. When you invest in yourself and the therapy process you will undoubtedly yield positive results. I look forward to connecting and beginning our work together.

I'm glad you're here. I provide couples/marriage and individual therapy to address relationship issues, trauma, infidelity, anxiety/depression, infidelity, navigating open relationships/polyamory. You may feel like you are having the same fight over and over again or walking on eggshells in your marriage/relationship. You may feel like the relationship you want is not possible or that you will never be able to get back to the way things were before. I can help you get to the root of the disconnection, help you slow things down, and address concerns in a safe, supportive environment.Three words that describe my therapeutic style: safe, compassionate, and encouraging. I use evidence-based treatments, such as Emotionally Focused Therapy and Gottman Method, which have over 40 years of research behind them. I use a non-pathologizing approach- all of you is welcome here, including all relationship styles.Together we will work to de-escalate arguments, improve communication, repair past hurts, and increase friendship and trust. Please call or email for a free 15 minute consultation appointment to see if we’d be a good fit. I look forward to hearing from you.

I am an experienced Marriage and Family Therapist.  Therapy is the best medicine for working through life changes that may be painful and difficult. I provide a safe environment for you to share your experiences and work on problems in your life.  I offer services for men and women dealing with depression, anxiety, grief or loss. I assist couple's ready to resolve differences and deepen their commitment to one another. I welcome clients from all walks of life and provide open and honest feedback and support.I am trained in Neurofeedback and Hypnotherapy. I specialize in depression, anxiety, PTSD, ADHD and ADD.  Neurofeedback is an excellent alternative to ADD/ADHD medicine and antidepressants.I am open to new clients and can take United Behavioral Health (UBH), Aetna Insurance and TriWest Healthcare Alliance for military and their families.  Feel free to call to interview me so that you can decide if I'm the right therapist for you.

If you feel unfulfilled in your relationships and find loss and change difficult, and if you want to get to the source of the patterns and blocks keeping you stuck in worry, anxiety, emotional eating, lost sleep, and a lack of faith, then I can help. I especially enjoy working with couples and individuals longing for a connection to their "soul's wisdom" so that they can feel more balance, joy, and fulfillment.  I am an integrative, holistic mind-body-spirit psychotherapist. I offer techniques that will help you tune into your deepest self, the part of you that has your best wisdom and answers for what you are seeking in your life.I specialize in treating anxiety and panic attacks, phobias, PTSD, eating disorders, trauma recovery, sexual abuse recovery, OCD, depression, and couples therapy,   I offer therapy groups, including:   (1) Self-Discovery: Transforming the Shadow Within (2) Authentic Relationship Skills group for adults who find it difficult to relate to others authentically.I provide a variety of experiential techniques, including EMDR, guided visualization, Somatic Experiencing, hypnotherapy, Brainspotting, mindfulness practices and spiritual processes to guide you back to your intuitive knowing and soul-wisdom. As well, I have extensive experience in couples therapy and pre-marital counseling.
